title: texas omelet(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Layer sausage or bacon, cheese and bread in cake pan.
Combine eggs, milk and spices; mix well.
Pour liquid mixture over bread, cheese and meat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: beefy nachos
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Heat to blend spices and meat mixture.
Place nacho chips on a cookie sheet; top with meat mixture, then dribble Ranch dressing on top of meat.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° only until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or use cream cheese icing.

title: walnut squash cake
directions: In large bowl combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer on medium speed, beat sugar and butter until smooth.
Beat in the oil, juice, eggs and vanilla.
Reduce mixer to low.
Beat flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in squash until well mixed.
Divide batter in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake for 30 minute at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes before removing them from pans.

title: sausage snack wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 16 triangles.
Cut each triangle into thirds lengthwise.
Place 1 sausage on each triangle.
Roll up, starting with shortest side of triangle. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 48 appetizers.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir.
With wire whisk, stir in sugar, flour, vanilla, salt and milk.
Mix in pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown cut up fryer in hot fat. Add enough cold water to cover chicken (about 2 qt.). Cook until chicken is tender; add just enough salt to taste. Beat eggs; add enough flour for a thick dough. Roll real thin on floured paper; cut small pieces and add to chicken broth.

title: strawberry wonder dessert
directions: Prepare gelatin using 1 cup boiling water. Stir in frozen strawberries and chill until syrupy. Prepare pudding using 1 cup cold milk.
Beat in ice cream.
Tear cake into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding mixture over cake, then pour strawberry mixture over pudding. Chill.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour all beans and browned meat in crock-pot.
Then mix the last 3 ingredients with beans and meat.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: blackberry sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, tapioca and berries.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Spread sour cream over berries. Combine crumbs, remaining sugar, melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in jar or plastic container.
Add 2 to 3 Tbsp. to hot water, mix, and enjoy!

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 6 cups of flour and beat well.
Add about 6 cups flour until stiff.
Knead well on floured board, adding more flour if it sticks to board.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Slice tops off of bell peppers and clean and wash. Place bell peppers in large pot of water with salt and parboil until they change colors and tender. In a large pot mix ground beef, bell peppers, meat tenderizer, garlic powder, onion and cook on medium heat until done. Drain grease. Add rice and tomato sauce. Cover and cook on medium heat until rice is tender. Remove whole bell peppers from water. Place in
13 X 9 baking dish and spoon mixture into bell peppers until rounded on top. Mix 2 cans tomato soup and 1 can hot

water. Spoon soup mixture over bell peppers. If you have any meat mixture left after filling peppers spoon around bell peppers and spoon soup mixture over that. Cover and bake in a preheated oven at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Remove cover and serve.

title: divinity
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook and stir over medium heat to boiling.
Cook without stirring to 260°, hard ball stage (10 to 15 minutes.)
Remove from heat.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions but omit salt and add onion.
Drain; save cooking liquid.
Mix flour with part of milk mixture until smooth.
Add remaining liquid to broccoli.
Stir in flour mixture, fat and seasonings.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until soup is slightly thickened and flavors are blended.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked egg, if desired.

title: golden wedding rings
directions: Blend cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add chopped nuts and pineapple.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups of sandwich filling.

title: million dollar candy
directions: Mix.
Shake in a sealed container and use in recipes calling for Eagle Brand condensed milk.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup and cheese over low heat until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into well-oiled mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: everyday salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
May be kept in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions; set aside. Combine evaporated milk and ground beef; mix together well. Divide meat into 5 patties and put 1/4 cup of stuffing into center of each. Fold meat over stuffing and seal edges. Put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and water. Pour over bundles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large, deep skillet or Dutch oven, heat butter.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute 5 minutes, until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups water, stirring until smooth.
Return to heat.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat to simmer. Cook, covered, but stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serve, sprinkled with additional chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Place graham crackers in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix other ingredients except pie filling together with an electric mixer. Pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Let set in refrigerator, or you can freeze.
After cream cheese layer has set, pour pie filling over top.

title: hasty oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and margarine.
Let stand 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients to oatmeal mixture.
Mix by hand.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Tastes best when refrigerated overnight.

title: kielbasa potato dish
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large skillet; fry until potatoes are tender.
Add corn.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Easy and fast. Serves 6.

title: pickled pineapple slices
directions: In a large skillet combine, pineapple syrup, sugar, vinegar and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir 10 minutes. Stick each slice with a clove and add to skillet.
Simmer 20 minutes, basting frequently with syrup.
Remove from heat.
Cool. Put in jars and cover tightly.
Keep refrigerated up to 2 months. To give away, pack in tight fitting lid and jar.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt butter; stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt. Pour into bowl with mixed cereals and nuts.
Stir until evenly coated.
Heat on sheet cake pan at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add potato, water, bouillon cubes and salt.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add celery, carrot, pepper, turnip, parsnip and tomato.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Just before serving, stir in the parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat.
Make Sauce:
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in flour and bouillon.
Add milk, water and wine. Cook until thick.
Set aside.

title: honey butter
directions: Allow butter to stand at room temperature until soft, then thoroughly mix with the honey (either by using a blender or mixer).
Cover with tight lid and allow to solidify in the refrigerator.
After that, the honey butter need not be refrigerated.

title: tangy cucumbers and onions
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in medium size bowl.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and vinegar.
May add some milk to thin if necessary.
Pour over cucumbers and onions; refrigerate.

title: 5-minute fat-free chili
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients (except garnish). Simmer over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Garnish with grated cheese and onion, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion; continue to saute until onion is tender.
Drain excess fat.
Combine bacon and onion with beans and remaining ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 50 to
55 minutes.

title: spiced cider
directions: Mix ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Turn off heat. Let stand several hours.
Shake well.
Strain and serve hot or cold.

title: easy bread
directions: Mix well and put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Good Seasons according to directions, except using 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1/4 cup water to the oil.
Add McCormick Salad Seasoning.
Mix vegetables with spaghetti and pour dressing over.
Chill overnight.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: If using crab, rinse in colander and remove all shell and cartilage.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix by hand; chill and form into balls.
Roll into chopped pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: fried chicken wings
directions: Mix marinade ingredients.
Add chicken; turn once for 12 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a foil lined pan. Drain.
Replace in oven and bake until crisp.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add cheese, garlic mix and milk.
Keep warm in fondue pot.
Serve with chips.
(Fritos are excellent with this.)

title: beef roast
directions: If 3 pound roast, mix the salt, pepper and brown sugar and rub well into all sides of the meat.
Place in casserole.
Add a small amount of water (approximately 3 tablespoons).
Roast at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cover until done.
(Roasting time is approximately 30 to 35 minutes per pound of beef.
If it is a boneless, rolled roast, increase time about 10 minutes per pound.)

title: dried apple cakes
directions: Cook dried apples in 4 cups water until tender.
Drain and save juice.
Measure 2 cups juice, adding water if needed.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with dry baking mix.
Stir in sourdough starter to moisten flour.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead lightly. Pat or roll to a 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with apples. Roll, starting at short end.
Cut into 12 slices.
Put remaining sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, butter and the 2 cups apple liquid into a large deep skillet.
Bring to boil.
Gently lower apple slices into hot syrup.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian fried dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Place teaspoon each in hot oil until golden.
Drain; sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: pickled corn cobs
directions: Trim cobs and let stand in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours. Drain.
Chill in cold water.
Make a syrup of vinegar, sugar and spices tied in a cheesecloth bag.
Bring to boiling point and add corn cobs.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Fill sterilized jars with cobs and liquid.
Seal and store in a cool dark place.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with sour cream and pudding mix.
Pour mixture in a graham cracker crust and top with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Put jelly and barbecue sauce in crock-pot. Add frozen meatballs. Cook on low until meatballs are warm, then serve.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Beat next 3 ingredients and spread on first mixture.
Beat the lemon pudding mix and milk together until it begins to thicken.
Spread over cheese mixture and spread Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle crushed nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: london sponge
directions: On waxed paper, sift together 3 times, 1/2 cup of the sugar and the cornstarch.
In a large bowl beat together the whites of the eggs, cream of tartar and water until soft peaks form.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat just until blended.
Fold in sugar/cornstarch mixture a little at a time, until no dry particles are visible.
Bake in 2 ungreased 8 x 1 1/4-inch round cake pans in a preheated 350° oven until top springs back when lightly touched (about 30 minutes).
Cool in pans on wire racks.
Loosen edges and ease out.
Fill with jam.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: mama kail's boiled cookies
directions: In 10-inch cast-iron skillet, combine the sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and boil exactly 90 seconds.
Immediately remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.

title: chocolate pound cake - fudge icing
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, about 1/3 at a time, beating constantly. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix up and serve cold.

title: boiled irish soda cake
directions: Boil water, raisins and applesauce 10 minutes.
Add butter and let stand until cold.
Add to boiled mixture the eggs and mix.
Add all dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Stir in molasses.
Bake in greased, floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 1/4 hours (test; ovens vary).
(Some take longer.)
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: mango bread
directions: Peel mangos and chop.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Place crushed pretzels in bowl.
Add melted oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: argentine club sandwich
directions: Place cooked meats on bread.
Sprinkle Blue cheese over meats. Add cooked bacon.
Spread mayonnaise on one slice of bread and enjoy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1/3 cup berries.
Add water and sugar.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes.
Soften cornstarch with water and add to mix.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High.
Stir once.
Stir in butter and cool. Fill shell with remaining berries.
Pour cooled glaze over top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter in a saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage and add peanut butter.
Mix, then pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain and rinse with warm water to rinse off fat.
Add oregano, basil, catsup, salt, pepper, mushrooms and Franco American spaghetti.
Stir to mix well and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Can be served with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: super stuffed clams
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the bacon.
Use enough bread crumbs to absorb the liquid.
Fill individual shells.
Chop the bacon and put a few bits on each stuffed clam shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then broil until the bacon crisps.
Makes approximately 12 shells.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter. Add eggs and sour cream. Stir in both kinds of corn, salt and muffin mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set. Knife in center should be clean. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: grace biscuits
directions: Preheat oven 425°, arrange shelf one slot below center of the oven.
Spray 8 or 9 in cake pan with spray.
In large bowl, stir together self-rising flour, sugar, salt.
Work shortening in with your fingers until no large lumps.
Gently stir in cream, then buttermilk.
Dough should not be soupy but be wet and resemble cottage cheese.
Spread all-purpose flour on a plate or pie pan. With a medium spoon, drop 3 scoops of dough well apart in the flour.
Shake flour gently over the scoops of dough.
Flour your hands, pick up a dough ball, gently shape into a round, shaking off excess flour and place in the prepared cake pan.
Continue with the remaining dough, placing each biscuit closely to each other in the pan.
Bake until lightly brown 20-25 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Invert biscuits on plate and serve.

title: spinach and ham roll-ups
directions: Combine soup,
sour
cream
and
mustard
mixing
well. Divide into 1/2 portions.
Take
of
the soup mixture and blend in spinach, rice, cottage cheese, eggs, onion and flour. Mix
all together well.
Spoon 1 heaping tablespoonful of the spinach mixture
onto one square of ham slice.
Roll up.
Put seam
side down in a 15 x 9-inch dish sprayed beforehand with Pam.
Spoon remaining
soup mixture onto squares and continue until
all
ham has been used.
Pour last half of soup mixture over
the
ham rolls.
Sprinkle
buttered
cracker crumbs and parsley
over
the top.
Bake
uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let
sit
for 10
minutes
before serving.
(Can be frozen in advance of cooking.)

title: brownie pizza
directions: Prepare 1 package brownie mix as directed on box.
Pour onto a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until set. Cool.
Spread frosting on cooled brownies.
Top with chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, M&M's candies and marshmallows.
Pour chocolate syrup over top.

title: peach cake
directions: Drain large can peaches.
Save 1/2 cup peach juice.
Add chopped peaches to first mixture.
Add peach juice and mix well. Bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars. Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add oats, chips and nuts. Drop on greased or nonstick cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Heat all ingredients except coconut and pecans in small saucepan. Simmer until smooth; beat until thick enough to spread. Add coconut and pecans. Cool slightly before icing cake.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, chilies and onion in a large bowl. Dip half the tortillas in soup mixture, then place in 9-inch round casserole. Sprinkle with 3/4 of the cheese.
Dip remaining tortillas in the soup mixture and place in casserole. Pour remainder of soup mixture over the casserole. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Steam broccoli, carrots and celery until tender.
Puree in blender or food processor with 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Pour into large saucepan and add remaining 2 cups chicken broth.

title: cocoa fudge cake(club member: ashley wilson)
directions: Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Measure all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Pour into pans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Frost and serve.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix walnuts, cinnamon and sugar, set aside.

Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs, sour cream, milk and vanilla. Mix well. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Pour 1\2 batter into a Tube pan. Sprinkle 1\2 nut mixture over batter. Pour remaining batter. Sprinkle remaining nut mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 40-50 min.
Check for consistency, if too soft bake a bit longer.

title: wylina's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, well beaten eggs, syrup and nuts; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: gouda grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook grits according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Garnish with paprika and grate more Gouda on top.
Place under broiler to melt.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Mix soda into buttermilk.
Mix candy with 1/2 c. flour.
Alternate flour and buttermilk, stirring after each addition.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Stir candy into batter.
Add coconut last.
Bake in 13 x 9 inch greased and floured pan for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt 1 package mild Cracker Barrel cheese. Thin it with sherry. Add 1 cup crabmeat. Blend. Serve on Triscuits or tortilla chips.

title: blueberry bake
directions: Unroll 1 can of rolls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Pinch edges together.
Cream sugar, egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Spread over the rolls that were placed in baking dish.
Spread blueberry pie filling over the cream cheese mixture.
Unroll the other can of rolls and place on top of this mixture.
Brush with egg white. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is light brown.

title: lime jello dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and extract; chill for about 1 1/2 hours, until slightly thickened. Measure 1 3/4 cups gelatin into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; chill for about 5 minutes.
Blend Cool Whip into remaining gelatin. Carefully spoon 1/3 of the creamy mixture into the pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cookie crumbs.
Repeat these 2 layers; spoon the remaining creamy mixture on top.
Chill until firm.
Serve.

title: homemade soup
directions: Brown meat and pour off grease.
Cut potatoes and carrots as desired.
Pour in about 6 cups water, depending on size of pot. Add other ingredients and cook for about 45 minutes.
Cook on medium-high.

title: no-fat creamy french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Process using a pulsing motion in order to blend all ingredients, yet retain some tomato texture.
Chill 15 minutes before serving. Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Melt caramels and water in double boiler.
Add corn syrup if desired.
Pour over cooked popcorn and toss until well coated. Shape into balls.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured bread pans for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Continue to cream until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, mayonnaise, mushroom soup, eggs and chopped onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over top.
In a frypan, melt butter and mix in stuffing.
Put stuffing mixture on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: powdered sugar replacement(sugar free)
directions: Sift all of the ingredients and place in an airtight container for future use.
When I get all the things out and have all the mess I usually make a double batch then I am done with it for a while.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix with a spoon.
Mix slowly into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins with spoon.

title: easy reese's cookies
directions: Slice and halve dough according to directions on package. Place cookie dough in miniature muffin tin; bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and rap lightly on counter to make cookies fall.
Top each cookie with a Reese's cup; return to oven for 4 minutes, or until it begins to melt.
This makes about 40 to 45.

title: macaroni sweet and sour salad(yields 12 servings)
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add egg and mix.
Add melted butter, vinegar and water. Put on burner and cook, stirring continuously until it comes to a boil.
Take off burner and let cool.
Pour over macaroni.

title: mark's taco dip
directions: Using a large platter, pat a layer of beans on platter.
Mix sour cream and taco mix and layer mixture on top of beans.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except for the cheeses, together and layer on top of the sour cream.
Top with the shredded cheeses. Put taco chips around the edge of the platter.

title: crunch cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: makes its own crust egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 9-inch pie plate with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy-day stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in pan large enough to hold them in single layer.
Cut potatoes, carrots, onions and celery in good-size chunks and layer on top of meat.
Mix tomato sauce with 1 can water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Scatter 2 teaspoons quick-cook tapioca on top. Seal tightly with heavy foil; place in 325° oven for at least 2 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain excess oil.
Combine cream cheese, soup, milk, catsup and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Add to ground beef.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Place can of biscuits on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Serves six.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and syrup with melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Add pecans to syrup; mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Pie is done when center of pie shakes a little.

title: apple butter
directions: Put cooked apples (prepared by slicing, peeling and cooking on low with a small amount of water until tender), sugar and vinegar in slow cooker (crock-pot). Cover and cook mixture 12 hours on low.
Add spices and cook for 3 hours on high without lid or until mixture becomes a spreading consistency.
Fill refrigerator containers or put into sterilized jar and seal with a canner.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Heat milk and water to 120° and add yeast; set aside.
In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups of the flour and all other dry ingredients.
Add milk and water; mix well with fork or spoon. Add the other 2 1/2 cups flour and mix.
Spoon into two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans which have been greased and dusted with corn meal.
Sprinkle corn meal on top.
Raise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Remove from pans and let cool.
Slice, toast and enjoy.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
In large pot, add 8 to 10 cups water, beef bouillon cubes and browned hamburger.
Add all ingredients in pot.
Simmer in covered pot until well done.

title: self-rising flour rolls
directions: Add sugar to the water, then add yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Add yeast mixture to flour.
Mix well and let rise until double. Punch down; make into rolls.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued fish
directions: Place fish fillets in ungreased baking
pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Mix catsup, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, onion, salt and pepper sauce. Pour on fish. Turn until both sides are coated. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla and blend together.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients; shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Place Hershey's Kisses on cookies and return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: baked spinach tomatoes
directions: Cut top 1/4 off tomatoes.
Scoop out.
Sprinkle insides with salt and sugar.
Invert tomatoes and drain.
Cook spinach briefly. Press water out.
Saute onion in butter.
Add flour.
Stir until blended, then add milk.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Add spinach, salt and pepper.
Fill tomatoes.
Can sprinkle tops with buttered crumbs or Parmesan cheese.
Prepare ahead, but do not bake up to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Crush cereal.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.

title: banana loaf or muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Cream butter, sugar and egg; add bananas.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add to banana mixture with milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add apple juice and chill until syrupy.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: westhaven cake
directions: Cut dates in pieces and add to water and soda.
Boil and let cool.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add sifted ingredients and date mixture alternately to the cream mixture.

title: fruited ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add ginger ale. Cool. Add fruits. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: millet with chickpea and vegetable stew
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and margarine and saute the onions with salt for about 2 to 3 minutes or until onion softens. Add the mushrooms, lemon juice and broccoli.
Cover and cook the mixture over medium-low heat for about 10 minutes or until broccoli is bright green and just tender.
Add chickpeas, currants, paprika, pepper and cayenne and simmer, covered, for another 1 to 2 minutes to heat through.
Serve over cooked millet.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and 2 cups of sugar.
Add the five egg yolks, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat thoroughly.
Then add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Beat smooth after each addition.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and add final cup of sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold into the batter. Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: 3-layer dessert
directions: First Layer: Press the flour, margarine and nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ring fudge
directions: Melt bits with condensed milk over boiling water until mix begins to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla; blend well.
Chill about 1 hour.
Line bottom of a 9-inch pie pan with foil.
Place nut halves in the bottom.
Spread chocolate mix over nuts to form ring.
Put nuts on top.
Chill.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Saute celery and shallots in butter.
Add soup which has been heated with Philadelphia cream cheese and rest of ingredients. Pour into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish. Cover. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: bass fritters
directions: Separate eggs.
Chop garlic and parsley.
Poach fish in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Remove and mash fish.
Beat egg yolks; add flour.
Stir in seasonings, garlic, parsley and fish. Beat egg whites until frothy; fold into fish mixture.
Drop spoonfuls into hot oil (should be at 360° and 2 1/2-inches deep). Fry until golden.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, soup and preserves well. Line baking dish with foil and lay chicken out in single layer. Pour mixture over chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lazy day salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the hand the fruit cocktail, oranges, pineapple and pudding mixes.
Mix well, and fold in whipped topping.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: cowboy corn bread
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper in skillet until desired brownness.
Mix the rest of ingredients in bowl.
Drain sausage, onions and green peppers and add to other ingredients and place in baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, at 350° for about 1 hour.
Excellent with dry beans!

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Whip ingredients, except Cool Whip, on low until mixed.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Put in freezer for 4 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak pieces in flour and cook in oil until brown. Saut celery, bell pepper and onion and combine with steak pieces. Combine diced tomatoes (rinse cans with water and add to tomatoes - a lot of liquid is needed), tomato juice, taco sauce, mushrooms and seasonings. Add steak and sauteed vegetables. Put into a 2 1/2-inch deep 10 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° until steak is tender (approximately 1 hour). Juice will thicken as it bakes. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Cover with aluminum foil for the last 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow the directions of Solomon for bringing up a child; Proverbs 23:14; that is, "Beat him with a rod."
Bake as a loaf cake at 325° for about 50 minutes. Cool on rack.
Slices best after a few hours.
(All references are to the King James version of the Bible.)

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; slowly stir in the milk. Cook and stir until mixture is boiling and thickened.
Blend small amounts of hot mixture into the slightly beaten yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add the butter, lemon peel and the lemon juice.
Cover and cool.
Fold in the sour cream.

title: pineapple icing for cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and pineapple; then add eggs.
Cook until heavy and thick and falls off spoon.
Spread on cooled cake and sprinkle with coconut.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Combine mustard, vinegar and water until there are no lumps. Pour into small saucepan; add sugar and egg yolk.
Stir well over medium heat until thick (like gravy); cool.

title: dove and dumplings
directions: Place dove in a large deep pot and cover with water.
Add salt, carrot, onion and stalk celery.
Boil until dove is tender, about 2 hours.
Remove dove and strain broth.
Mix biscuit dough as directed and pat out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch pieces.
Drop into gently boiling broth.
Boil gently about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook a few dumplings at a time.

title: quiche
directions: Layer grated cheeses into pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Top with browned sausage.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: peach crisp
directions: Arrange peach slices in an 8 inch square dish or pan.
Set aside.
Combine next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 18 to 20
minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been greased.
Place cheese on top of croutons.
Fry sausage and drain. Place on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk together.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight. In morning, pour 1/2 cup milk mixed with soup on top.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix all the remaining sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour half of batter in a greased angel food or Bundt cake pan and add half of the cinnamon mixture.
Add the remaining batter and top with the cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: mix flour and sugar, combine with butter and eggs.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is done.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Lightly but thoroughly, stir in cottage cheese, flour and salt.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto buttered hot griddle.
Bake until bubbles appear on surface and bottom is golden brown.
Turn pancakes.
Bake until brown and serve.

title: heath delight
directions: Prepare cake and pudding as directed.
Crumble half of cake in a dish, then pour half of pudding on cake.
Crumble a layer of Heath bars, then do again with rest of cake, then pudding, then Heath bars.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle some Heath bar on top.
Refrigerate.

title: artichoke hearts soup
directions: In a soup pan, saute onion until golden brown.
Add veggie broth and finely chopped artichoke hearts.
Cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Remove from the heat and puree.
Serve hot with grated cheese.
Serves 10.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Stir the onion soup mix into sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with vegetable tray.

title: kolacky
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese in large bowl. Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until smooth and creamy. Beat in vanilla. Combine flour and salt in a small bowl. Gradually add to margarine mixture, beating until mixture forms soft dough. Divide dough in half; wrap each half in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Pour cold water over yeast and let stand.
Using an electric mixer, combine sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Continue beating and add boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Add yeast mixture, flour and salt, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to use, punch down dough and knead lightly.
Shape into balls and place in greased muffin pans.
Brush lightly with melted butter. Let rise until double in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.
These rolls can be left in refrigerator and used as needed.
This recipe is one that, when you use it once, you will love it and always come back to it again and again.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Warm buttermilk, mix sugar and yeast together and then add to buttermilk.
Add melted shortening (not hot).
Add flour mixture to which salt, baking powder and soda have been added. Mix well. Knead a little.
Make into small balls and put into greased baking dish.
Let rise 45 minutes or until double in size.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Do not drain bacon.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: challet ham dip
directions: Thoroughly combine first four ingredients.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.

title: caramel marshmallow balls
directions: Melt butter, caramels and sweetened condensed milk in medium pan over low heat. Dip each marshmallow into melted mixture and roll in Rice Krispies. Cool individually on waxed paper. Store in container, NOT AIRTIGHT or they will get sticky.

title: tarragon chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add chicken and melon balls; toss.
Serve on lettuce.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease bottom of cake pan.
Cover bottom of pan with chopped pecans and coconut.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Cream together cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Pour this mixture over cake and swirl together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak red beans overnight.
Put into Dutch oven, meats, beans and vegetables.
Simmer until beans are soft.
Serve over rice.

title: dietetic cake(for diabetics)
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is gone.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener, salt and oil and mix well by hand.
Blend in soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in greased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour. Freezes well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for one hour in a 375° oven.

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Saut butter and onion until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add to spinach, artichoke hearts, cream cheese, sour cream, both cheeses and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake about 25 minutes at 325°.
Enjoy.

title: pasta chicken salad
directions: The dressing is made of equal parts of Hellmann's mayo, Miracle Whip and sour cream. Add a large dose of Old Bay seasoning.
Chill well before serving. (I make it the evening prior to serving.)

title: eggplant salad spread
directions: Wrap eggplant in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until soft.
Remove skin.
Mash with other ingredients.
Serve on bread, crackers and/or pita bread.

title: red cabbage salad
directions: In a large bowl mix cabbage, onion & sugar. Set aside. In a small saucepan combine remaining ingredients, bring to a boil 30 seconds until mustard has melted. Pour over cabbage. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch in large pan; stir in water and apple juice.
Boil.
Add rhubarb; return to boil.
Cook 5 minutes or until rhubarb is tender and thick.
Pour into 9-inch dish.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in saucepan over medium heat.
Add all ingredients. Cook until rice is done.
Add water as needed.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients over hot water in double boiler. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Set aside to cool.
Blend margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla, beating until light. Sift flour, soda and salt together, then add to first mix of margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Press 2/3 of mixture into a 9 x 9 or 7 x 11 pan that's been greased and floured.
Spread chocolate mixture over batter, then top with remaining batter by crumbles or bits over chocolate (use fingers and pat down a little).
Sprinkle with nuts and press into top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: round steak supper
directions: Cut round steak into serving-sized pieces; season with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Cook onions in hot fat until tender, but not brown.
Remove onions.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, save juice. Put into large bowl, add marshmallows and cubed apples. Do not peel. Mix pineapple juice and brown sugar until sugar dissolves. Pour over fruit and stir gently. Add peanuts. Fold in whipped topping. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours. Before serving. This makes a very large bowl.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in a rectangular cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes (depending on how well done you like it).

title: jibin syrian cheese
directions: Heat milk over medium heat until lukewarm (110°).
Remove from heat and add rennet which has been crushed and dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Break mixture with spoon. Return to low heat, stirring constantly until a firm curd is formed.
Pour approximately 2 cups into strainer and drain as much water as possible.
Form into a ball and press into a thick pattie.
Salt both sides and let drain.
Refrigerate.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Empty jello in small bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in medium size bowl.
Crush graham crackers and add melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Empty 2/3 of crumbs in a 10-inch baking dish or pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Press into even layer on bottom of pan.
When lemon mixture begins to thicken, add lemon juice to chilled milk.
Whip until stiff and holds peaks.
Fold into jello mixture lightly but thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix altogether. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Crisscross with a fork dipped in flour. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: strawberry soup
directions: In processor, puree strawberries thoroughly.
Add cider or juice, cinnamon, honey, sugar and nutmeg.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: First, use care to get one.
Not too young; but tender and a healthy growth.
Make your selection carefully and let it be final.
Otherwise they will not keep.
Like wine, they improve with age.
Do not pickle or put in hot water.
This makes them sour.
Prepare as follows:
Sweeten with smiles according to variety.
The sour, bitter kind are improved by a pinch of salt of common sense.
Spice with patience.
Wrap well in a mantle of charity.
Preserve over a good fire of steady devotion.
Serve with peaches and cream.
The poorest varieties may be improved by this process and kept for years in any climate.

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine rice with beef, egg, onion, salt, marjoram, pepper and 1/2 cup of tomato juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape mixture into 18 balls and place in deep skillet.
Add sugar to remaining 2 cups of tomato juice.
Pour juice over meat balls in skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: coconut ice cream delight
directions: Scoop vanilla ice cream into balls.
Roll in toasted coconut and pack lightly as you roll.
Put in plastic container and freeze.
When ready to serve, place 3 toasted coconut balls in a dish, stripe with syrup and top with dab of Cool Whip.

title: caramel pecan ice cream
directions: Boil both cans of Eagle Brand milk in enough water to cover the cans for 3 hours.
Let milk cool.
Beat eggs; pour half and half in slowly; add Eagle Brand, whipping cream and sugar.
Blend well and pour in freezer container.
Finish with whole milk.

title: yeast raised donuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream sugar, shortening, nutmeg and salt.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flours and baking powder and add.
Add milk slowly. Do not make dough too soft.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Roll out and cut with a donut cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 350°.
Dip cooked donuts in Sugar Glaze.

title: strawberry iced brie
directions: Ice top and sides of fresh Brie with softened strawberry cheese.
Decorate with fresh strawberries and greenery.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: corn spoon bread(sweet corn cake)
directions: In nonstick skillet, combine corn, milk, milk powder, 1 tablespoon honey, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Cook over medium heat until liquid is absorbed and corn is brown and sticky, stirring constantly. Preheat oven to 325°; spray 1-quart baking dish with cooking spray.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot on low setting.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: venison steaks braised in red wine(servings:  8)
directions: Marinate meat before cooking.
Put in a dish with room for marinade.
Peel and slice onions, shallots and garlic.
Scatter vegetables over meat with cloves, bay leaves and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour vinegar and oil over top.
Leave to marinate 3 to 4 days, turning meat over every day.
On day of cooking, cut bacon into strips.
Cook until browned and rendered of fat in flame-proof casserole.
Drain the venison, reserving the marinade, and add to casserole.
Brown on all sides over medium heat.
Add the red wine, stock and 1 cup of strained marinade.
Cover the casserole and simmer over a very low heat for one hour.
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix thoroughly using a fork to avoid packing.
Place in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off excess fat.
Place on a hot platter and arrange a buttered vegetable such as small boiled potatoes, onions or sliced carrots around the meat loaf.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil, sour cream and eggs in large bowl; set aside.
In small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans.

title: double trouble fudge
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt the semi-sweet chocolate pieces with 2/3 cup of the sweetened condensed milk, 1 tablespoon of the cream and 1 teaspoon of the vanilla.
Remove from heat when thoroughly melted and spread evenly into a foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
In another saucepan over low heat, combine the remaining ingredients and heat until thoroughly melted.
Remove from the heat; spread evenly over the layer already in the 9-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours.
Turn fudge over and out onto a cutting board; slice to appropriate size.

title: my homemade ice cream
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, vanilla and 1 can of Pet milk together in freezer.
Add the second can of Pet milk and then fill the remainder of the freezer with whole milk.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Heat marshmallows in concentrate until melted.
Cool; add ginger ale.
Mix in a mold between broken up angel food cake pieces.
Chill.
Serve with whipping cream, whipped topping, chocolate sauce or whatever.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl. Pour half of the batter in the pan (warm pan).
Sprinkle half the cheese over the batter, spread remaining batter over the mixture and top with the rest of the cheese.
Bake for about 35 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Add raisins to boiling water and simmer 5 minutes.
Add together to the raisins and water the sugar, brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook slow boil 1 minute at a rolling boil. Add lemon juice and orange juice.
Dot with butter.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: cottage cheese orange jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
One-half cup nuts may be added if desired.
Pour in mold or desired container and refrigerate.
Also tasty with lemon jello.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and raisins.
Mix cornstarch and eggs.
Stir into milk mixture.
Cook until thickens.
Add rice and raisins. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: black pepper cookies
directions: In a large
bowl,
sift
together flour, sugar, spices, cocoa and baking
powder.
In
another bowl, cream shortening; add eggs (slightly beaten).
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients a little at
a
time.
Add nuts, etc., if desired. Drop onto ungreased cookie
sheets 1 teaspoon at a time.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes;
cool
on wire rack.
Dust with sifted confectioners sugar.
Can be frozen for storage.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Beat egg yolks with remaining sugar; add rest of ingredients and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line jelly roll pan (with sides on) with waxed paper.
Pour above mixture in pan and bake at 350°
for about 18 minutes.
Dump pan over on towel and roll in towel and cool on rack.

title: harvard beets
directions: In a double boiler or heavy boiler mix sugar, salt and corn starch,
stir in vinegar.
Add onion, oleo and the juice from the beets.
Blend well and cook until smooth.
Add the beets and simmer for 20 minutes.
This keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; stir in flour, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well; mold into balls about one-inch in diameter. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. While cookies are still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash and drain vegetables.
Remove seed from peppers.
Peel onions.
Chop all vegetables.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Cover again with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, salt and spices (tied in bag) to vinegar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add vegetables; simmer 10 minutes. Bring to boiling.
Pack, boiling hot, into hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: sausage and cajun rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a Dutch oven; remove and drain on paper towels.
Drain off drippings, reserving 1 tablespoon in Dutch oven.
Saute onion in reserved drippings, 3 to 5 minutes; add sausage, cabbage and water.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Stir in carrots and potatoes; cover and cook an additional 20 minutes or until they are tender.
Serves 8.

title: granny smith's apple dip
directions: Mix all together; serve at room temperature with sliced apples.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Heat corn syrup in microwave until hot but not yet boiling. Stir syrup into coconut until completely mixed.
Let mixture sit for about 2 hours.
Shape into balls; chill in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together; mix well.
Dip coconut/syrup balls in chocolate.
Drop onto waxed paper; let chocolate set. Serve.

title: freezer rhubarb strawberry jam
directions: Cook rhubarb until tender. Add Jell-O, stirring well to dissolve. Pour into containers. Cool and freeze.

title: cindy's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; cool.
Mix cooked hamburger with 2 jars Prego sauce.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, spoonfuls of cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Continue until you use everything.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered, until cheese starts to brown.

title: canned green beans
directions: Mix water, vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil. Add beans and boil for 30 minutes.
Put in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; fold in pineapple, strawberries, pecans and bananas.
Put half of mixture (about 3 cups) in refrigerator about 1 1/2 hours, leaving half of mixture at room temperature.
Spread the sour cream gently over the congealed half and add remaining mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: upside down german chocolate cake
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut over melted butter.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour over coconut.	Then mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar and spoon into cake mixture, keeping away from sides.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 325° or until knife inserted comes out clean. Let cool and then turn upside down.

title: whip up a cream that won't sink(polly's pointers)
directions: This stabilized whipped cream tastes great!
This will hold up even overnight in the refrigerator!
It's perfect when you want to prepare cream topping or a filled dessert ahead of time.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together by hand exactly as listed above in large bowl and pour into greased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken; layer in a large casserole dish. Slice eggs on top of chicken.
Spread peas (drained) and corn (drained).
Add cream of chicken soup with the chicken broth and pour on vegetables.
Mix together flour, butter and milk; pour evenly on top.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: You will need 4 sheets of waxed paper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla extract in a mixing bowl until fluffy.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in zucchini and nuts. Put into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Cool before serving.

title: oriental fried rice
directions: Spray wok or skillet with Pam.
Melt butter in pan; saute onions in butter until tender.
Add ham and cook until browned. Move onions and ham to one side of pan.
Scramble eggs in empty space.

title: chicken supreme(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Heat 1 to 2 cups oil in Dutch oven.
Cut chicken into pieces (remove skin if you like); pat dry.
Mix flour, salt and garlic powder in a small bowl or Ziploc bag.
Coat chicken in flour mixture.
Brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken from oil; pour oil out of Dutch oven into a heat-resistant can.
Place chicken back into Dutch oven.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and water.
Cover Dutch oven with lid; place on heat.
Cook for about 1 hour, or until chicken is tender and cooked through.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with half lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
Brown in butter in skillet.
Dissolve granules in boiling water; add, with remaining lemon juice, to skillet.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: summer pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet. Brown in oven.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise and spread on crust.
Top with the other ingredients as desired.

title: microwave caponato(eggplant appetizer)
directions: Cut unpeeled eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes.
Pour oil into a 2-quart casserole with cover; heat in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in eggplant.
Cover with lid; cook on High for 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in onion, celery and green pepper. Cover; cook on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, olives, vinegar, sugar, capers, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Serve at room temperature or chilled. Flavor improves upon standing.
Serve with pita wedges, crackers or toast triangles.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Mix and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Crush cranberry sauce with fork.
Soften gelatin in cold water; heat over boiling water until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir into cranberry sauce; cool slightly.
Add lemon juice and ginger ale; mix well.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and walnuts.
Put into lightly oiled 2-quart ring mold.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In each of two (11 x 7 x 1-inch) baking dishes, layer 1 cup spaghetti sauce mixture, 2 noodles and 1 1/4 cups cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, spaghetti sauce mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: dilled garden dip
directions: Place cottage cheese and vinegar in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Top with cover and process until smooth.
Combine cottage cheese mixture, green onions and next 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well.

title: special k bars
directions: In a double boiler, bring the Karo syrup and sugar to a boil. When boiling, add the peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add this mixture to the Rice Krispies and Special K.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: robin roy cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Mix water and vanilla together.
Add both to sifted flour.
Add pecans.
Mix with hands; shape into walnut-size balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: easy custard pie
directions: *Sprinkle on top of pie before putting in oven.

title: broccoli and celery quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onion and celery in margarine. Lightly beat eggs and Coffee-mate.
Add other ingredients and pour into pastry shells.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic salt; drain.
Add onion, soup, mild taco sauce, salt and chili powder.
In baking dish, layer tortillas and ground beef.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in pan. Add salt. Cover with water and ice for an hour. Drain and wash. Mix sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar. Bring to a boil. When boiling, pour over squash and boil 2 to 4 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: quick foil dinner with ham
directions: The amount of food needed will be determined by how many foil dinners you need.

title: people chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Put cereal in large mixing bowl and pour chocolate mixture over it.
Mix well.
Place 2 to 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar in a paper sack.
Pour cereal mixture into sack and shake to coat.

title: coffeepot punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar in coffee pot.
Place cinnamon and cloves in basket.
Perk.

title: barbecue pork or hamburger
directions: If using hamburger brown with onions.
For pork, cook roast until done then mince.
Cook onions in margarine.
Add other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until most of the water boils out.

(Leave some water in). Cut the Velveeta into chunks and drop into macaroni to melt. Add margarine and evaporated milk. Simmer until cheese and margarine are melted. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted or lightly brown.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Leave a little lumpy.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Pour out onto griddle, about 350°.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Spread pecans in bottom of pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into 8 pieces.
Dip each piece in melted margarine.
Roll each piece in cinnamon sugar. Layer into pan.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening; mix.
Add milk; mix well.
Roll out dough; cut into small squares or pull apart in pieces.
Place into stew.
Cook for 12 minutes only.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine milk and burnt sugar syrup.
Add alternately with flour which has been sifted with baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured pan in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup for one mug of boiling water.

title: sugar cinnamon loaf
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald milk; add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour, mixing well.
Add yeast and eggs, beating well.
Then add enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place in lightly greased bowl; turn once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size (about 2 hours).

title: fabulous christmas punch or red punch
directions: Puree berries in blender.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, then stir in lemon concentrate until melted.
Add cold water and juice.
Pour over ice.
Before serving add ginger ale (a good brand please).

title: amish fried cucumbers
directions: Beat egg and add milk.
Peel and slice cucumbers.
Dip slices in cracker crumbs.
Lay them out to dry a little, then dip in egg and milk mixture followed by crumbs again.
Fry in butter or vegetable oil, then salt and pepper.

title: spinach casserole(serves 6)
directions: Put all the ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs or potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Gently mix in cherries.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 4 hours at least before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut up chicken in small cubes.
Cook spaghetti, rinse and drain.
In a large oblong dish put cooked spaghetti, chicken, broth, mayonnaise, milk, chopped celery, onions, lemon juice, almonds and chopped boiled eggs; mix well.
Spread out evenly. Grate cheese and spread over top of mixture.
Crunch up potato chips and spread over cheese.
Bake for about 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds, in a large saucepan. Cook on medium-high until cranberries "pop", about 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in almonds.
Serve chilled.
Keeps very well in refrigearator for several days.

title: snow cream
directions: Start with chilled bowl.
Beat eggs and sugar, adding cream gradually, until fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Then add clean, white snow until thickness of ice cream.
Serve gently.

title: jenny mayberry's success oriented
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Preheat a large skillet over highest heat until very hot.
Add oil and scramble eggs.
Add cooked rice and vegetables.
Stir and toss to blend quickly.
Add sesame oil and soy sauce and optional ingredients, if desired.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Melt cream cheese and tomato soup in double boiler.
Add gelatine to dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill in mold.
Serve with crackers (I like Triscuits).

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat slightly in skillet; season with onion salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order given. Rinse out tomato can with water and pour over all.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on high until steaming, then on low for about 30 minutes.

title: braised beef with mushrooms
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic in shortening. Add remaining ingredients except mushrooms. Simmer until beef is tender. Add mushrooms and heat through. Pour over noodles or spaghetti.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter; stir until butter melts.
Cover and boil mixture for 3 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and without stirring, add remaining butter, pecans, peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat mixture until well blended and pour immediately into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut fudge into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: zucchini meat casserole
directions: Take medium size squash, wash and cut lengthway.
Scoop out seed and pack with any of the ingredients.
Bake until squash is tender, about 1 hour.
Be sure to precook any of the stuffings. Cover before baking.

title: turkey and ham in cream sauce
directions: Heat butter in chafing dish or skillet; blend in flour, salt, dry
mustard
and
pepper.	Heat until mixture bubbles, stirring constantly.
Remove
from
heat;
gradually
stir in chicken broth and cream.	Return to heat and boil rapidly 1 or 2	minutes, stirring.
Add
hot
sauce to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Blend at	once
and
add	to
mixture in pan;
cook 2 minutes on	low heat.
Add turkey, ham and ripe olives.
Heat through.
Serve
on toast points, waffles or in patty shells. May also	be
layered with macaroni in a casserole.
End with cream sauce layer.	Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini squash relish
directions: Mix squash and onions; sprinkle salt and mix well.
Let stand overnight in cool place.
Drain and rinse with cool water.
Place all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to boil for 3 to 5 minutes. Cook squash until changes color.
Put in jars; seal.
May add red or green peppers for color.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make 2-inch balls.
Let stand for 1 hour. Brown in oven 15 minutes.

title: roasted potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Scrub potatoes; cut each lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Place butter and oil into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; set in oven to melt butter.
Add potatoes; toss to coat well with butter mixture.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake for 1 hour or until tender, turning potatoes occasionally.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread.
Spread pudding in 9 x 12-inch pan and dot with 1/2 stick of butter.
Cut bread dough in small chunks.
Dip in remaining butter (melted), then in brown sugar/cinnamon mixture, then in pecans.
Place in pan on top of pudding and butter.
Leave at room temperature overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Mix squash, onions and green pepper.
Add salt and put in a large pan.
Cover with ice water.
Let stand 3 hours.
Mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Boil 2 minutes.
Put into sterile jars. Seal.
Let set one week.
Chill before serving.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chocolate lovers sheet cake brownies
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and sugar; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt and bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water. Add milk, vinegar, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and pour over sugar and flour.
Mix this with a spoon.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. Check with a toothpick.

title: artichoke heart casserole
directions: In a saucepan saute onion in olive oil until golden and tender.
Add artichokes and stir over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Stirring often, add cheeses and bread crumbs.
Mix well. Pour into well greased casserole.
Sprinkle with a little bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: bits 'o brickle bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Crisco.
Pat into the bottom of a jelly roll pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over mixture and cover with Bits 'O Brickle.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine the sugar and flour.
Stir in water until smooth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat.
Add the gelatin and lemon juice; stir until dissolved.
Allow to cool to room temperature, about 30 minutes. Add the strawberries and stir gently to coat.
Spoon into the pastry shell.
Chill until set, about 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix ingredients for cake together and place in a tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour on lower shelf.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let potatoes thaw slightly.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Place in sprayed 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until bubbly and golden brown on top.
Add a few crushed potato chips after baking.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add grated carrots.
Add sifted flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix nuts, dates, raisins and bread crumbs and add to mixture.
Steam 2 hours in a shortening can or quart fruit jars with lids.
Don't fill the containers more than half to 3/4 full to allow for expansion.
The sealed fruit jars will keep several months.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to directions.
Cool completely. Crumble in bottom of 9 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan or dish.
Layer on top of cornbread, the kidney beans (washed and drained), then peppers, onions, tomatoes and bacon bits.
Whip mayonnaise and cover the rest of the salad.
Save a little of the cornbread and crumble it on the top just before putting the mayonnaise on it.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix flour, milk and sugar; pour into pan. Pour fruit over batter.
Cook 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: cube steak special
directions: Cut up large onions to taste in crock pot.
Place cube steaks in pot.
Cover with one can of beer (alcohol evaporates while cooking).
Simmer gently 4-6 hours until tender.
Thicken with package of beef gravy mix as desired.

title: champion chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar. Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips.
Press firmly in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except popcorn.
In a heavy saucepan, bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook to 250° on a candy thermometer.
Mixture will bubble up in pan; watch it to keep from boiling over.
Pour slowly onto hot popcorn and mix until well coated.
Let stand 5 minutes or until mixture can be easily formed into balls.
Butter hands and form into 3-inch balls.
Makes 18 balls.

title: german potato soup
directions: Made with skim milk, there is no fat or cholesterol.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and curry powder; bring to a boil.
Drain the fruit.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish and pour hot sauce over it.
Garnish with cherries.
Bake at 325° until it bubbles (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Serve hot.
Very good with poultry, cured ham and pork.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Combine flour and cocoa and blend into creamed mixture.
Add pecans; beat on low speed until blended.
Chill dough about 1 hour.

title: pink artic freeze
directions: Mix all together with electric beater, then fold in whipped heavy cream.
Turn into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3 or mold).
Freeze until firm. Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and freeze in cartons.
To serve, let set out of freezer about 1 hour before serving.
Chop up mixture and add ginger ale.
Serves 20.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg and combine with flour and soda.
Stir in baking bits, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13-15 minutes.
Cool 2-3 minutes on sheet before removing to racks to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry waffles
directions: Heat frozen waffles as directed on package.
Top each with scoop of ice cream.
Spoon berries over ice cream.

title: swiss cheese dill puffs
directions: In the microwave oven in a 1-quart nonmetal casserole, cook butter or margarine, uncovered, on High powder for 1 1/4 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in shredded Swiss cheese, milk, snipped chives and dillweed.
Microwave, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until cheese is melted, stirring mixture once during cooking.
Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: pennsylvania applesauce bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, put all ingredients except nuts.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in loaf pans which have been greased on the bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Stir and cook evaporated milk and sugar for 6 minutes.
After it boils, take off heat.
Stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
(Set marshmallow cream in hot water to soften while sugar and milk are cooling.)
Grease pans and line with wax paper.
Pour fudge in pans and let stand 8 hours.
Remove off wax paper and cut.
Yield:
5 pounds.

title: lemon-ginger drumsticks
directions: To reduce unsaturated fat and calories, remove chicken skin. Rinse chicken with cold water.
(Carefully clean hands and all surfaces to reduce risks related to salmonella bacteria from raw chicken.)
In large, shallow baking dish, arrange chicken.
In small bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours or overnight.
Prepare grill or broiler for cooking.
Lightly brush rack with vegetable oil.
Grill chicken 20 to 30 minutes, occasionally turning and basting with remaining marinade.
Chicken is done if juices run clear when pierced.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; do not add salt.
Pick it off the bone; set aside.
Save chicken broth.
Melt margarine; stir into dressing. Save some dressing for top.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make sauce by combining barbecue sauce, sugar, 1 tablespoon of lemon juice and mustard in a small bowl. Set aside.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour well.
Add pecans and shape into fingers.
Flatten just a little.
Place on brown paper and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still hot.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Pour sauce over it and bake in an uncovered oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: curried lamb stew(adapted from the barnard inn)
directions: In a shallow bowl, blend the flour, curry, salt and pepper. Roll the lamb in flour mixture.
In a casserole dish, heat the oil.
Brown the lamb; remove and keep warm.
Saute onion.
Return the lamb to the casserole and sprinkle with remaining flour mixture.
Pour the liquids over the meat and mix well.
Add raisins, lemon juice and apples and cook, partially covered, until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice, chutney and yogurt-cucumber salad.
Serves 4.

title: dark chocolate cake with peanut butter frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda in bowl. Set aside. In another bowl, mix water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Add previous dry mix to wet. Mix. Stir quickly. Don't overmix. Pour in pan. Bake approximately 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Mix milk, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla to frost cake. You can add more peanut butter for stronger taste.

title: baked pasta primavera
directions: Grease a large baking dish.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse.
Toss with oil.
Spoon into a large bowl.

title: orange delight
directions: Pour boiling water over jello to dissolve.
Mix sherbet into hot jello with eggbeater.
Leave slightly lumpy.
Dice in banana and marshmallows.
Mix so marshmallows are coated with liquid. Let stand until cool.
Place in refrigerator.
Sets quickly.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. Serve over crisp salad greens.

title: two tone fudge
directions: Over moderate heat, melt butter, sugars, and canned milk together.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour half of hot mixture over butterscotch pieces, stirring until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour in buttered pan/dish.
Pour remainder of hot mixture over chocolate pieces, stirring until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour over top of butterscotch.

title: lazy galompki
directions: Lay some cabbage leaves in bottom of pan.
Saute onions, mushrooms and whatever else you want to add.
Cook the rice. Saute the hamburger meat.
Add onion mixture, eggs, rice and some chopped cabbage leaves.
Lay this mixture on top of the cabbage leaves in pan.
Top with rest of cabbage leaves.
Pour tomato juice over all.
Layer strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° until bacon is cooked, then everything else will be done.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Mix all.
Keep at room temperature for 6 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
Replace in jar.
Refrigerate.

title: bolivian fritos
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out; cut into strips and deep fry until brown in hot oil.

title: ambrosia hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together a day ahead of use so marshmallows will absorb pineapple juice.

title: chinese raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars; mix well.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs.
Mix.
Add flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Bake until lightly brown 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven on greased baking sheets.
Bon appetit!

title: salmon casserole
directions: Drain salmon and mash into chunks.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1 can of milk.
Blend and spread in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Cook in 350° oven until it bubbles.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: In a large bowl with a wooden spoon, mix in order given.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Ice immediately.

title: tropical fruit brunch parfait
directions: Drain tropical fruit salad.
