Combine cottage cheese, yogurt and raisins.
Layer in 4 glasses cottage cheese mixture, fruit salad and granola.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix.
Shape into a mold and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: dustin's choco-no-bake cookies
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Let dry for several hours.

title: raspberry cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped almonds.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Fry wings.
Sprinkle wings with hot sauce and roll them around until well coated.
Serve with Ranch dressing for dipping.

title: broiled icing
directions: Mix butter and milk.
Add brown sugar and boil 1 minute.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour over cake and brown lightly.

title: baked eggs
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Arrange bread (cut in quarters) in 2 layers.
Spread mushrooms and sausage over bread. Pour beaten eggs, milk and salt all over.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix well and pour into shallow pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with Powdered Sugar Icing or substitute peanut butter for part of butter in icing recipe to top with Peanut Butter Frosting.
Cocoa may be added to this.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine the cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 cup cream of coconut, 1/2 cup rum, oil and eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes. Stir in pineapple.
Pour into prepared pan and bake until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto a cooling rack. With a skewer, poke holes about 1-inch apart in cake, going almost to the bottom.
Combine remaining cream of coconut and remaining rum.
Slowly spoon over cake.
Chill thoroughly.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water until limp.
Drain and set aside.
Combine beef, onion, rice, egg, salt and pepper in bowl and mix well.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves, being careful to fold in sides and tuck in ends.
Place in slow cooker.
Stir pepper flakes (if used) and sugar into tomato sauce and pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover pot and set at low.
Cook 10 hours or set on automatic and cook 8 hours or until you're ready.

title: grandmama cogle's sunday vegetable soup
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Dice meat.
In large boiler, pour tomatoes and mash into small pieces.
Add 2 cans cream of chicken soup and mix with tomatoes.
Turn the heat on medium and begin to heat mixture slowly, stirring as you add the other ingredients. Allow mixture to heat after each vegetable is added.
Add beans and liquid, creamed and whole corn.
Continue to heat thoroughly.
Add diced chicken pieces, salt and pepper to taste.
Also, add 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburg and onion.
Add other ingredients, mix together and cook.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken.
Heat through. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: I make this ahead for the holidays!

title: enchilada bake
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture. Place rolled tortillas in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl except for grated cheese.
Pour sour cream mixture over top of tortillas.
Add grated cheese over this.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: round steak with gravy
directions: Cut steak into 5 or 6 serving pieces.
Place in slow cooking pot.
Add dry onion soup mix, water and mushroom soup. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Great when served with mashed potatoes.

title: chip dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender. Serve!

title: cindy's spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute olive oil, onion and garlic until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Pour mixture over cooked spaghetti.

title: aunt martha's sausage casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain, then add to drained sausage.
Add succotash.
Mix mushroom soup and milk, then stir into mixture. Pour into casserole; sprinkle generously with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese for 2 minutes until creamy. Gradually add sugar at medium speed and beat 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat just until yellow disappears. Gradually add flour beating at lowest speed until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavoring, chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: date roll
directions: Put milk and sugar over fire and allow to boil until a soft ball is formed.
Add dates before removing.
Allow to cool.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour on damp cloth.
Shape into roll.
Roll in powdered sugar and slice.

title: apples in a blanket
directions: Cut apples in half and wrap each half with a rolled out biscuit.
Place wrapped apples in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings in a Dutch oven until tender. Add okra and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until okra is tender.

title: plum good bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast walnuts on a baking sheet in preheated oven 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Watch carefully, they burn easily.
Set aside.

title: prune cake
directions: Heat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease generously and lightly dust tube pan with flour.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, sugar, nutmeg, allspice, and cinnamon.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add nuts, prunes, and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: country cornbread
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into greased 5-inch cast-iron skillet.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: mana
directions: Grind the nuts and place in a bowl.
Mix in the grated lemon rind and sugar.
Fold in the 2 egg yolks (save whites in a bowl) and the whole egg; knead until all ingredients are well incorporated.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese into a large mixing bowl.
Add pimentos.
In a small saucepan, beat 1 egg.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook until thickened.
Add butter, then add all to cheese and beat with mixer until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar and 1 cup orange juice in container of electric blender; process until smooth.

title: silver queen corn pudding
directions: Put corn into food processor, pulse until finely chopped. Place in colander and drain 1 hour.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour corn mixture into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet relish
directions: Mix lime in 1 gal. water; soak cucumbers overnight. Drain and rinse. Soak cucumbers in ice water 2 to 3 hours; drain. Mix sugar, vinegar, water and salt; heat. Place pickling spice in a small bag; add cucumbers and pickling spice to vinegar mixture. Cook 40 to 45 minutes. Add a little mustard seed just before placing in sterile jars. Seal jars while hot.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread in a cookie sheet with a rim (spread very thin, about 1/3-inch thick).
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven and, while hot, cover with 6 Hershey bars (no almonds).
Spread evenly and cover with chopped pecans.
Cut into approximately 1-inch squares (diamond design) while still warm.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet. Stir until crumbling; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and 1 1/2 cups water, mixing well.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally, adding more water if needed.
Serve immediately.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks oleo in saucepan.
Beat egg and 1/2 cup milk; add sugar. Add to melted oleo and bring to a boil, stirring all the time. Take off and add chopped nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs. Pour this over crackers in pan.
Cover with another layer of whole crackers.
Top with powdered sugar, 1 stick melted oleo, 3 tablespoons milk and vanilla.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet (light brown).
Place in oblong pan. Cover with cream of chicken soup. Bake about 1 hour at 450°. Good served with Minute rice.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Combine with celery.
Pour boiling water over and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain well and squeeze out excess water.
Add rest of ingredients and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Pickling spice may be added if desired.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs and oil.
Pour one-half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the batter.
Add the other half of batter. Bake at 350° until done.
Punch holes in the cake while warm and pour on a glaze of:

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls (size of a walnut); place on cookie sheet.
Mash with fork; sprinkle with sugar and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Dissolve gelatin in water. Add sugar and pineapple juice; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add pineapple.
Chill until partially thickened and/or jelled. Fold in Dream Whip.

title: quick barbecued chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine the ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, onion, celery seed, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper flakes and liquid smoke if desired. Cook and stir over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Roll in balls. Dip in sugar.
Flatten with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: strawberries and cream cheese freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs and water; blend with mixer 2 minutes or until creamy.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Pour in 1/3 batter; sprinkle 1/2 of Jell-O around.
Pour in some more batter and sprinkle in rest of Jell-O.
Pour in rest of batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: basic cream pie filling
directions: Coconut Pie:
Add 1/2 cup coconut to filling.
Sprinkle a little coconut on top of meringue before baking.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well (at least 5 minutes) after each egg.
Pour into pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: yum-yum potatoes
directions: Coat potatoes with oil.
Place raw potatoes and remaining oil if any in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over potatoes. Bake at 450° until done, about 40 minutes, mixing occasionally. Smells and tastes heavenly.

title: fresh fruit cheese pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill 3 hours. Slice a variety of fruits and arrange on top of cheese pie.

title: my friend's potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and toss well. Refrigerate.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Stir mayonnaise and flour in a 2-quart saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thickened. Stir in turkey and vegetables.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Place pie crust over casserole (pressing edges to seal).
Cut several holes in crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water; cook until plump and drain, but leave a small amount of liquid on them.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, sour cream, cornstarch, salt and vanilla.
Add this to raisins and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° until meringue is brown.
Also good with Cool Whip instead of meringue.

title: king casserole
directions: Heat canned ingredients to bubbling.
Add chicken.
In large casserole dish, line with a layer of chips.
Sprinkle cheese and add soup mixture.
Layer another layer of chips, cheese and soup, ending with soup on top.
Cover with remaining cheese and bake until bubbling.

title: chicken rodeo
directions: Combine
flour,
cooking oil, paprika, salt and pepper; dip chicken in it.
Arrange in a shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients;
pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Delicious served with rice!

title: congealed cherry salad
directions: Heat pie filling and sugar.
Add water.
Stir well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
(If you use Comstock pie filling, reduce sugar to 1/2 cup.)
Put in refrigerator for several hours.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until medium stiff.
Drop egg yolks into cold water.
Beat until foamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating continuously.
Sift cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold sifted mixture into egg yolk and add vanilla or lemon.
Stir egg whites and fold in.
Use tube pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Invert when done.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add vegetables and pasta and water.
Cover; simmer 7 to 9 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation Time:
20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until fluffy.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain, cool and set aside.
Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
This will be the first layer.
Second layer is onion and tomato.
Third layer is ground beef.
Fourth layer is cheese, tortilla chips and dressing.
Chips and dressing should not be put on salad until ready to serve.

title: perfect divinity
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°), stirring only until sugar dissolves.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. When syrup reaches 236°, gradually add half the syrup to egg whites, beating at high speed on electric mixer.
Cook remaining syrup to hard ball stage (250°) slowly add to the egg white mixture, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and beat until candy holds its shape (about 5 minutes).
If desired, add chopped candied cherries.
Drop pillows of candy from a teaspoonful onto waxed paper, swirling tops.
Makes about 3 dozen pieces of candy.

title: hot vegetable dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cheeses with mixer.
Fold in onion, green pepper and chipped beef.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: putting on the ritz
directions: Combine pecans, chopped dates and condensed milk.
Cook on low heat until thickens.
Spread 1 teaspoon mixture on each Ritz cracker.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cook.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crescents
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form in round balls and then into crescent shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry cherry pie
directions: Prepare pie crust for 2-crust pie in 9-inch pie pan.
Heat oven to 425°.

title: chicken with vegetables in wine
directions: Brown chicken and garlic in oil; add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking until most of liquid is gone.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn chowder
directions: Boil potatoes. When boiling, add diced onion and celery. Fry bacon, break and set aside. Add corn, milk, flour, salt and pepper. Stir in bacon. Heat well, but do not boil. More milk may be added, if desired.

title: 15 bean stew mom's style
directions: In a large deep pot, put chicken broth, onion and bouillon cubes; basil, oregano and sage should be put in at this time unless you are using bay leaf, then omit basil, oregano and sage.
Boil for 1 hour.
Add Oriental seasoning and beans (unsoaked).
Cook on medium heat 1 1/2 hours, then turn off heat and let cook until your supper (about 2 hours) in its own heat, covered.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Cook to soft boil.
Cool until you can place your hand under the pan.
Beat.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: breakfast squares
directions: Break bread into pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage, then cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard and pour over layers.
Mix soup and water and pour over all.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; spread bread slices with butter. Place on a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside. Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt; mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from fridge 15 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Use trifle bowl and layer all ingredients, starting with lettuce on bottom, then onion slices, peas, celery and bell pepper (all colors if desired), then bacon.
Take one cup mayonnaise; smooth across top to seal.
Sprinkle mayonnaise with 1 teaspoon sugar and grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover and chill 24 hours; toss just before serving.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Mix together; add dressing.
Toss.
Serve with lettuce. Serves 6.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Let Philly soften at room temperature.
When soft, add lemon juice and vanilla with fork.
Blend together, then add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix with blender 2 to 3 minutes.
You will have some small lumps.
Pour into pie crust.
Put lid on.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, then put cherries on top.
Strawberries or blueberries, any topping will do.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples, core and cut into eighths. Arrange in pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples. Mix 1/3 cup sugar with flour, cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 35-45 minutes until done. If pie browns too quickly, cover edge with foil. Cool. Pass with whipped cream, if desired.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boil.
Dissolve Jello in pineapple.
Cool to room temperature.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip, and pecans. Refrigerate to jell.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in greased casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup, milk and water.
Pour over chops.
Place sliced onion on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 45 minutes.
If this is cooked in crock-pot, do not add any water.

title: yangtze beef(steak-on-stick)
directions: In a medium glass bowl, combine the soy sauce, brown sugar, oil, ginger, pepper and garlic.
Set aside and slice meat into 1/4-inch thick strips.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Cook stuffing as directed on box.
Put a spoonful of stuffing on each slice of turkey and roll up. Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over turkey rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk and sugar.
Add a little milk to the cornstarch to make a paste, then add to the egg mixture.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla.
Cover with wax paper until completely cold.
Add peanut butter.
Mix with hand mixer until well blended.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Combine ingredients. Refrigerate until served.

title: ground beef and potato pie
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in skillet.
Add potatoes and ground beef.
Cook until ground beef is brown and crumbly, stirring frequently; drain.
Add 1/2 cup milk, mushrooms, soup, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Blend baking mix and 1 cup milk in bowl.
Spoon over ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut brittle (microwave)
directions: (Use wooden spoon or non-melting utensils)

title: chicken and pork adobo
directions: Combine the ingredients and soak the chicken and pork for 30 minutes, then add 1/2 cup water and simmer until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine; spread over rectangle.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; add nuts if you'd like.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and secure with toothpicks. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour; drain.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar. Pour over water chestnuts and bake another 1/2 hour or less.

title: chicken soup chinese style
directions: Finely slice white part of onions.
Reserve green parts for garnish.
Heat stock until boiling.
Add mushrooms and onions. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken.
Beat eggs with a little salt and pepper until frothy.
Stir soup well.
Pour eggs steadily into soup, stirring constantly, so that it remains in shreds.
Let cook a minute or two to set eggs.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Serve in soup bowls.
Sprinkle with finely chopped green parts of onions. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: country market bean soup
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain off water, leaving beans in Dutch oven; add water, chicken broth and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar and let stand overnight.
Mix pineapple and marshmallows and let stand overnight.
Next day, add Cool Whip; mix all together and freeze.

title: sugar-n-spice coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease two 8-inch cake pans.
Combine brown sugar, pecans, cereal and cinnamon; set aside.
Prepare cake mix using water required on package; add sour cream and eggs. Place 1 cup batter into each pan; cover batter in each pan with 3/4 cup cereal mixture.
Divide remaining batter between cake pans.
To the remaining cereal mixture, stir in 2 tablespoons butter; spread over cake batter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with orange juice and orange peel. Add marshmallow cream and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Add strawberries after jello starts to set.
Add cream.
Add angel food cake.
Pour into medium size rectangular pan and allow to set several hours in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge(low calorie)
directions: Coat 8x8 pan with cooking spray.
Stir together sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Bring to boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat to medium low and cook 3 minutes.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line muffin pan with paper baking cups. Place one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cup.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with fruit of your choice and enjoy.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Split the loaf of French bread in half (put margarine on each side, if desired).
Brown the ground beef; drain.
Sprinkle garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and Italian seasoning on beef.
Stir the tomato sauce in with the beef.
Spread beef mixture on both sides of bread.
Add slices of tomato, pepperoni and onions on beef.
Add Mozzarella or Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix ingredients
well and cook on medium heat, stirring regularly for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: hot vanilla(great substitute for hot chocolate)
directions: In a saucepan, heat milk until very hot but not boiling.
Pour milk into a mug.
Add honey, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well. Serve immediately.

title: venison roast
directions: Remove all fat from venison roast; season with salt and pepper.
Wash salt pork to remove excess salt.
Line roasting pan with salt pork.
Place venison roast in pan.
Add the juice of 1 lemon, Worcestershire sauce, chopped onion and slices of remaining lemon.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours or until done, adding hot water as needed.

title: delicious cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients for cake.
Beat for 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This will make 3 layers. Frost with following recipe.

title: butter nut drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolk and flavoring.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with the juice and rinds.
Mix thoroughly; cover and refrigerate for easy handling.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg white slightly.
Spread nuts on waxed paper.
Roll dough into tiny balls; dip in egg white and roll in nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Press cherry on top of each and bake 25 minutes.
Makes 40.

title: punch bowl trifle
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package, using a 13 x 9 baking pan. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in 8 x 13 baking dish.

title: old fashioned potato
directions: Bake potato and while
hot,
chop in plate.
Add margarine, seasoning and cheese.
Top	with bacon bits, chopped ham and sour cream.
Very good.

title: spaghetti sauce with mushrooms
directions: Fry the sausages until brown.
Pour off grease and slice sausages in bite size pieces when cool.
Simmer the mushrooms, peppers and salad dressing in pan used for sausage.
Add the hamburger, salt, lemon pepper and diced sausage.
Cook over low heat until all is brown and has simmered for 30 minutes.
Pour the marinara sauce in and water if needed.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: ranch stew
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients, add browned meat that has been drained.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add juices and salt.
Chill.
Stir sugar into ground cranberries and oranges.
Let stand 15 minutes. Add everything to slightly thickened jello.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Sprinkle salt over meat mixture; let mixture simmer.
Peel potatoes and boil until done (soft).
Drain potatoes and mash them with a hand mixer, adding 1/4 cup milk and 1 tablespoon butter.
Drain meat mixture.
Place meat on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over the meat.
Drain asparagus and put over cheese.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over asparagus and then pour cream of mushroom soup on.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and add potatoes, then sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Place in the oven until cheese is melted.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before serving so it can set up.
Enjoy!

title: foolproof chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix with sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt. Let come to rolling boil, then boil for 90 seconds.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Let cool slightly.
Beat, then spread quickly. This icing covers a 9 x 13-inch cake or brownies.

title: strawberry dessert(ann maloy's)
directions: Spread 1/4-inch layer of vanilla wafer crumbs in a glass 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Pile well drained dry fruit over this. Press gently. Spread whipped cream over the fruit.
Sprinkle remaining vanilla wafer crumbs on top.
Chill overnight. Cut into squares and serve cold.
Makes 20 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Cool and drain off water.
Add mayo, condensed milk and salt and pepper to taste, then add vegetables.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, bouillon and seasonings.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, on top of rice with larger pieces on outer edge.

title: tender pot roast
directions: Moisten meat.
Put onion and garlic powder on.
Pierce with fork.
Place in a 3-quart microwave casserole.
Cover; microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Reduce to Medium for 25 minutes.
Turn meat over; arrange vegetables around meat.
Cover; microwave on Medium 25 to 35 more minutes, until meat and vegetables are done. Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes while making gravy, if desired.

title: shell lasagne
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour into food processor; add cheese and Tabasco and blend until smooth.

title: chicken-in-a-shell
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out insides of potatoes and reserve, leaving a thin shell.
Mash potatoes with butter.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into potato shells.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Arrange potatoes in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chuck wagon buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in buttermilk, sugar, salt, baking soda, oil and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make medium dough (slightly sticky).
Place dough in greased bowl. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use, up to 7 days. Punch down daily.
When ready to bake, shape desired amount of dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Arrange 1 inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: pumpkin lemon cream pie
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool 20 minutes. Blend together sour cream, brown sugar, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Spread sour cream mixture evenly over pie.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Serve warm or cold.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar and milk together.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: herbed mustard dressing
directions: Blend first five ingredients with hand held blender until smooth.
Stir in cheese, marjoram and pepper.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve over mixed salad.

title: french onion crescent squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 2 rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides to form crusts, sealing perforations.
Sprinkle 1 cup onions and 1 cup cheese over dough.

title: corn and sausage skillet bake
directions: Cook sausage in 10-inch skillet until well done.
Add remaining ingredients except cornbread mix.
Prepare cornbread mix as directed on package and spread evenly over top of sausage mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Add shrimp and cook until done.
Blend in soup and milk; heat through.
Stir in sour cream and paprika, being careful not to boil.
Season to taste. Serve over hot, cooked fettucini.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: date cookies
directions: Bring dates to boil in water, then cool.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Then put all the moist ingredients in.
Drop by a spoon on a greased sheet.
Bake in a 325° oven until done.

title: shrimp dejohn
directions: Melt margarine and butter in large 9 to 10-inch skillet.
Add garlic and wine and cook about 2 minutes.
Add shrimp, cook about 3 minutes; do not overcook.
In a pie plate, line cooked shrimp and several spoons of the drippings over shrimp.
Add remaining drippings to bread crumbs along with parsley and lemon juice.
Mix until all the crumbs are dampened.
Spread crumbs over shrimp. Broil until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Double for main entree.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put the ingredients in a large bowl in the order given.
Cover bowl well.
Let stand overnight.
Mix when ready to serve.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Freeze 5 to 7 cut up marshmallows or 1/2 cup miniature marshmallows.
Mix the evaporated milk, sugar, oleo and 12 marshmallows.
Boil until marshmallows melt; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Pour the chocolate chips and vanilla into hot mixture. Beat until creamy.
Add the nutmeats and the frozen marshmallows. Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: raspberry icebox dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine the gelatin and water; stir until gelatin is dissolved. Fold in the raspberries. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until syrupy.

title: microwave cheese-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop enough of stems to make 1/4 cup.
Arrange half of the mushroom caps stem side up in 1-quart casserole.
Cook covered on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Invert caps on paper towels to drain.
Repeat with remaining mushrooms.

title: good biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once.
Mix until dough follows fork.
Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Can cut out biscuits or drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add enough flour so you can roll dough out thin.
Cut into small squares.
I use a pizza cutter and it works great!
Drop into boiling broth and cook for 20 minutes. Do not make dough too stiff, let it be very tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook breasts in salted water with onion.
Save broth.
Spray or butter 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Separate chicken into pieces to cover bottom of pan.
Layer broccoli spears on top.
Mix soup and rice with milk.
Pour over steamed chicken and broccoli.
Mix stuffing mix and one cup broth.
Toss together then place on top of casserole.
Add Cheddar cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked baby lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and cover with fresh water. Add 1 teaspoon salt; cook until tender.
Drain and rinse under running hot water.	Put
into
casserole and dab on oleo.
Mix together remaining salt, sugar, dry mustard and molasses.
Mix into beans well.
Add	sour cream, mixing in lightly.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks; put in bowl.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix.
Whip 1 or 2 pints of whipping cream and add to fruit.
Reddi-Wip may be used instead of whipping cream.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Place on top of layers.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Mix thoroughly.
(You can change any of the vegetables to whatever you may like in a salad.)

title: mary ann's brownies
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar. Stir in 1/4 cup chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonfuls over batter. Cut through batter with a knife to swirl the cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Cut into bars. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: pork "n" bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: poppycock
directions: Mix nuts and popped corn in large roaster pan.
Combine sugar, butter and syrup in saucepan and boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Pour at once over popcorn and nuts.
Mix well quickly with wooden spoon until well coated.
Let stand until cool and dry, then break apart. Store in tightly covered container.
Salted nuts or peanuts my be used for less expense.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: *I prefer the regular pudding mix; it tastes better! Adjust the recipe accordingly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding nut meats last.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until a silver knife inserted in the center of filling comes out clean.

title: mace cake(a favorite with men)
directions: Cream butter thoroughly, then add sugar gradually, continuing to beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating at least one minute after each addition.
Continue beating well after all eggs are added and while sifting together flour and mace 3 times, add flour to creamed mixture and beat on medium speed until blended.
Spoon into a Bundt pan that has been generously greased with shortening and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Turn out of pan immediately.
Cool and serve uniced.

title: aunt grace's hickory nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add milk, flour, baking powder, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: addie's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cover top with foil for a while.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in milk; let rise 45 minutes.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar, shortening, egg and salt together; add to yeast mixture with lukewarm water and flour.
Mix well.
Let dough stand overnight in refrigerator.
Three hours before meal knead portion of dough needed.
Make rolls and place into greased pan to rise.

title: spinach dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave spinach 5 minutes and stir, then 5 more minutes on High and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until smooth.
You can add the orange juice and rind.
Use as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: asheville salad
directions: Heat soup and water.
Put in cheese when hot.
Stir until smooth.
Add gelatine to hot mixture; let cool.
Add vegetables and mayonnaise.
Pour into molds and let set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with vegetables until done.
Cool and remove chicken from bones.
Mix soup and milk together; stir until smooth.
Fold in sour cream and stir until smooth.
Layer chicken into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and then crumble dressing on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350° with foil on top but not sealed tightly.
Can leave in oven 1 hour after baked with oven shut off.
Serves 12.

title: robin's easy noodles(known as shepherd's noodles)
directions: Mix Ricotta, milk, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes, or until heated.
Toss Ricotta mixture and cheese with hot pasta.
Easy side dish or add cooked ground meat for hearty main dish.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg and milk.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Drop onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: best pound cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of tube pan. Cream shortening and butter. Add sugar and cream together. Add eggs one at a time while mixing. Stir baking powder into flour. Add to mixture, one cup at a time, alternating with milk. When well blended, add lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. DO NOT OPEN OVEN WHILE BAKING. Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes. Run knife around side of pan to loosen, then turn out on rack to cool.

title: miss iris' christmas rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and water.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, spices and soda.
Add to butter and sugar mixture; mix well.
Stir in pecans and dates.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes. Store in airtight tin containers.

title: lemon cheese icing
directions: Cream all ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into top of double boiler.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring often.
The mixture will become quite thin at first.
Continue cooking until it thickens almost like custard, sufficient to frost a three layer cake.
Especially good on a white layer cake.

title: zucchini carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs.
Add zucchini and carrots. In separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients and add gradually to zucchini-carrot mixture.
Stir in orange juice, rind and nuts. Bake in greased loaf or tube pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Check for doneness.
Cool and remove.

title: judy's hunter stew
directions: Brown hamburger.
Put all ingredients in large crock-pot. Cook all day.

title: holiday quiche
directions: Prepare unpricked pie crust on cookie sheet and bake 6 minutes at 450°.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Combine ham, hard-cooked eggs, both cheeses, beaten eggs, cream and pepper.
Sprinkle with peppers.
Pour in pie crust and bake 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown pepper in margarine.
Remove and set aside.
Brown steak, mushrooms and garlic in skillet.
Add oregano, catsup, sherry and one tomato.
Steam, covered until meat is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until just heated.
Serve over rice.

title: snicker pie
directions: Bake pie crusts according to package instructions and let cool completely.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients in the oil.
Cook the spinach according to package directions.
Drain, saving liquid. Add water to make 1 cup. Stir spinach and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine juice into the spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste and dash of pepper.
Add this to the meat.
Add the spinach with the remaining ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Top with meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and half of dry ingredients, then add milk.
Add remainder of dry ingredients and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow cake to cool for about 1 hour before removing from pan.
Will keep 1 to 1 1/2 weeks wrapped in refrigerator.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub the inside of the salad bowl with the garlic clove.
Tear the lettuce into bite size pieces, add to salad bowl.
Add lemon juice, toss.
Sprinkle salad with Parmesan cheese, bacon bits and croutons.
Add Caesar salad dressing, toss and serve.

title: beef cabbage casserole
directions: Line greased 3-quart casserole with 1/3 of the shredded cabbage. Brown onions with beef. Add salt and pepper.
Drain fat. Add cooked rice and 1/4 of the seasoned tomato.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs well and add sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and cinnamon.
Warm the milk and add to mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 300° and bake until knife inserted into middle of pie comes out clean.

title: hot cider wassail
directions: Simmer cider, lemons, cinnamon, cloves and brown sugar together for 15 minutes.
Add ginger ale and orange soda.
Serve hot.
Makes 30 servings.
(I put the cloves in the peel of the lemons.)

title: macaroni and ham casserole
directions: Saut bell pepper and onion in butter for 5 minutes. Add ham and continue cooking until thoroughly heated. Combine all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into large greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with cheese and return to the oven. Bake until cheese melts.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Layer ham and potatoes in crockpot. Cover with cheese. Spread cream of mushroom soup over top. Cook on low for 3 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Sift flour and salt and set aside.
Mix baking soda and water.
Mix everything together with 1 small can of pumpkin.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Measure all ingredients and have ready before starting.
Pour boiling water into blender.
Add butter or oleo, then sugar, then dry milk.
Blend once, briefly, and scrape down the sides of container.
Then blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Pour and let stand until cool and thickened.
Use immediately or cover and refrigerate.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Dice olives and peppers very fine.
Mix Hidden Valley mix and softened cream cheese.
Add olives and peppers to cream cheese mixture.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill.
Cut in half. Serve with taco sauce, cheese sauce or both to dip.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature. Cream butter and sugar; add flavoring. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour once. Mix alternately flour and whipping cream. Put in cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Do not open door while cake is cooking.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Place apples in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
In small mixing bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside 1 teaspoon of mixture. Mix well and sprinkle evenly over apples in dish.
In medium bowl, stir together flour and nutmeg; cut in margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of mixture; gently toss with fork until well blended.
Put over apples and press lightly.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add cracker crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: aunt velma's brownies
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, melt the margarine with the chocolate. Add the sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder and pecans. Sift flour mixture into the first mixture. Beat all by hand. Add vanilla and pour into a well-greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Combine creamed mixture and dry mixture. Drop onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water or sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni (large).
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain. Add and mix all remaining canned items in a large skillet over low heat.
Layer chips, meat mixture and cheese in a large casserole dish.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: laura's chocolate cake
directions: Follow directions on box and bake cake in 1 long cake pan. While cake is still hot, poke holes with fork, then pour Eagle Brand milk over.
When completely cool, spread with Cool Whip, then squeeze Hershey's syrup on top.

title: prejesnac
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into flat baking dish (about 10 x 15-inch) and bake for 35 minutes at 325° or until slightly browned.
Cut immediately into squares.
Delicious for main dish or hors d'oeuvres.
Other green vegetables may be substituted, or in combinations:
broccoli, Swiss chard, beet tops, zucchini or summer squash.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare raw apples and set aside.
Measure salad oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy with low speed on electric mixer.
Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour mixture at a time to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
When all flour has been added or when batter becomes very stiff, remove electric mixer.
Fold in chopped pecans and raw chopped apples. Spread evenly in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly and well. Combine flour and cinnamon and add to the egg and zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins and pour into three (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool on rack.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add Crisco, buttermilk and yeast. Mix well.
Roll and cut out
like biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven until golden brown.
(Mixture
may
be
placed in covered dish and kept in refrigerator for several
days
if you do not wish to use it all at one time.)

title: never fail chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Return to broth and let stand.
Mix flour, shortening, egg and water.
When soft, roll out in 3 parts. Let sheets of dough dry 20 minutes.
Cut and drop in boiling broth.
Cook until tender.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Soften butter using electric mixer.
Add flour to cheese mixture.
Mix well until mixture looks like butter.
Put into a cookie press.
Using star pattern, make long continuous bar down length of cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Be careful not to overbake.
Cut into desired lengths when first removing from oven.
May be stored for several weeks.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar until hot.
Pour mixture over onion, bell pepper and cucumbers.
Store in small containers and freeze.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg; add water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Combine the two mixtures, a little at a time, until dry ingredients are moist. Mold together with hands; chill before rolling or keep in the refrigerator as long as a week.
The dough can be frozen.
Makes two double-crust pieces and one 9-inch shell.

title: sex on the beach
directions: In tall glass, fill with ice and add vodka and peach Schnapps. Fill rest of glass with 1/2 orange juice and 1/2 cranberry.

title: buttermilk bread
directions: Scald buttermilk (it will appear curdled).
Stir in salt, sugar and margarine.
Soften yeast in warm water.
When buttermilk mixture has cooled, add softened yeast.
Add flour and baking soda; mix.
Let set two minutes; knead.
Let set another two minutes and knead again.
Let rise in a warm place until about doubled in size.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Boil together sugar and water.
Cool.
Mix in lemon juice, cranberry juice and orange juice.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. Add 1 large ginger ale soda.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Put the potatoes, milk, salt and pepper in the top of your double boiler over boiling water.
Cook for thirty minutes.
Pour this mixture into a baking dish.
Pour cream on top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over entire dish.
Bake at 350° for twenty minutes.

title: quick and easy cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). Lightly grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cheese. In another large bowl, beat together egg, milk and oil. Stir the flour/cheese mixture into the egg mixture, stirring until just moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into center of loaf comes out clean.

title: balmy banana bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a shallow baking dish; reserve remaining butter.
Peel and layer bananas in the buttered dish; drizzle with lime juice.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot bananas with remaining butter.
Bake for 30 minutes basting once or twice with sauce.
Remove bananas carefully with a long spatula.
Serve hot with sauce spooned on top.
Serves 8.
Per serving: 149 calories, 4 g fat, 8 mg. cholesterol.

title: crunchy pie crust
directions: These crusts
may be made well in advance of use.
Seal off in plastic bag and freeze.
Use anytime.

title: cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 round layer pans (8 x1 1/2-inch).
Blend dry cake mix, oil, butter, eggs and oranges with syrup in large bowl on low speed for 1/2 minute.
Blend on medium speed for 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs until light.
Add shortening and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and baking soda. Beat again.
Beating at low speed, add 1 cup of flour at a time. Beat at high speed until creamy and thick.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello and warm water, then add pudding.
Mix and bring to boil 1 minute.
Cool, mix, then add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.

title: indian spoonbread
directions: Mix corn, milk, Crisco, eggs, corn meal, soda and salt well. Pour half the batter into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Spread chilies over batter. Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over chilies. Pour remaining batter on top. Sprinkle with additional 1 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries until they burst.
Add sugar and cook until dissolved.
Soak gelatin in cold water and turn into cranberries. Let cook; add nuts, celery, grapes and pineapple.
This makes a pan 12 x 7 x 7-inch full.
Cut into squares and top with salad dressing and Cool Whip combined.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in Dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking until vegetables are tender, but not mushy, and juice is thickened. Stir occasionally. Serves 8.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs and 8 ounces grated Cheddar cheese.
Drizzle 1 stick butter (melted) over top and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put fat in large boiler; let melt.
Peel and chop onions.
Cook in hot fat until tender.
Stir as they cook.
Take off heat.
Cut meat into small pieces; add to fat and onions with tomatoes.
Add uncooked rice, vegetables, water, salt and pepper.
Return boiler to heat.
Stir as it begins to boil, then cover with lid.
Turn heat to low.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally as it cooks to keep from sticking.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and mix well. Add all other ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° until brown.

title: microwave herbed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes (peeling is optional).
Slice several times across the potatoes being sure you do not cut all the way through.

title: poulet saute creole(chicken)
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil, put in different pot.
Saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Add tomatoes, garlic and seasonings. Add to chicken.
Put in thyme, bay leaf and tomato juice.
Bring to boil 10 minutes.
Season to taste with Tabasco.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain kidney beans and butter beans.
Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Combine the 3 cans of beans with browned ingredients along with remainder of ingredients.
Mix well. Simmer in crock-pot on low all afternoon.

title: cowboy caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream cheese, eggs, green onions and fresh red pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Spread cream cheese on serving dish.
Spoon bean mixture evenly over cream cheese.
Arrange egg on bean mixture.
Sprinkle with green onions and red pepper.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Make a white sauce of butter, flour and milk. Place half of potatoes in a greased casserole and cover with half of the sauce and seasonings.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until top forms a brown crust and potatoes are done.

title: edible fingerpaint
directions: Place dry pudding and milk in plastic container and secure the lid.
Children will love to shake the container and listen to the sound as it changes to pudding.
Using fingers (and feet!) children create "tasty" pictures.
Clean up is easy; a lick of the fingers and it's all gone.

title: vegetable bar
directions: Roll out and pinch together on sheet pan and bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and peppers in large container; sprinkle with salt.
Add ice and cover.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place over low heat.
Keep turning over pickles until mixture reaches scalding (do not boil). Put in hot jars and seal.
Let stand 48 hours before eating. Makes 8 pints.

title: cabbage-burger bake
directions: Chop cabbage (about 8 cups).
Spread half in shallow baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Saute bacon just until fat starts to cook out.
Remove and drain; set aside.
Stir onion and rice into drippings in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until onion is soft and rice is lightly browned.
Spoon over cabbage in baking dish. Brown hamburger and sprinkle over rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Heat tomato juice with spaghetti sauce mix to boiling.
Pour over cabbage, stirring so sauce flows to bottom.
Top with bacon; cover.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more to crisp bacon. Makes 6 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix raisins and water; let stand overnight.
Next morning add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 3 (1 lb.) coffee cans (tall ones).
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350.
Freezes well.

title: three bean chili
directions: Heat water or broth in a large soup pot over medium heat for about 5 minutes, adding more liquid if necessary.
Add 7 cups water, tomato puree or paste, lentils, green pepper, yellow pepper, red kidney beans, pinto beans, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, cayenne pepper and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Beat eggs in a small mixer bowl. Gradually add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in melted butter.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: holiday salad
directions: Heat cherry and pineapple juice to boiling; add jello.
Stir well.
Slowly add Coke.
Add cream cheese in small pieces.
Add crushed pineapple, Bing cherries, nuts and celery.
Mix well. Pour into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Combine soda and buttermilk; stir until soda dissolves.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add walnuts and bananas, stirring well. Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove and cool on racks.

title: marbled cookie squares
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, brown sugar, oil, water and eggs together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Take out and cut with knife to marble.
Continue baking for 20 to 25 minutes more. Allow to cool, then cut into bars.

title: kiwi pizza
directions: Cook cookie on flat pan 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and put this mixture on cookie.
Arrange fruit on cookie and serve.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: In skillet brown chicken about 10 minutes; remove chicken from skillet.
Mix the rest of ingredients together.
Add to skillet cook until mixture boils and thickens stirring constantly. Return chicken to skillet. Cook until chicken is done.
Serve over rice and garnish with orange slices.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Marinate overnight.
Cook hamburg, then simmer in taco seasoning (refrigerate overnight). When ready to serve, combine marinade mixture and hamburg.
Add lettuce and Doritos; mix together.

title: favorite chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from broth, cool and then remove skin and bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan bring to a boil the broth and soup.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables lightly and drain.
Add cheese, soup and water.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Rice Krispies; pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and cream
until
fluffy.
Add	eggs,
one at a time, blending each until
smooth.
Add
cake
flour
to creamed mixture; add vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for
hours.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut up onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Roll steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in pot.
Pour in can of tomato sauce. Cook 3 to 5 hours on high.

title: ida's texas trash
directions: Melt butter, bacon drippings, Worcestershire, hot sauce, seasoned salt and Tabasco sauce and drizzle over remaining ingredients.
Put in a very slow oven (275°) for 1 hour.
Stir at 10 minute intervals from bottom of pan.

title: peach praline pie
directions: Combine sliced, peeled peaches, sugar, tapioca and lemon juice. Let stand 15 minutes. Combine flour, brown sugar and pecans. Cut in margarine with fork until

crumble. Sprinkle 1/3 of this mixture over bottom of crust. Cover with peach mixture. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over peaches. Bake at 450°F for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 20 minutes longer, or until peaches are tender and top is golden brown.

title: peanutty fudge
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together until blended.
Add sugar to make a stiff dough.
Knead with hands to blend well.
Knead in nuts.
Press into a well buttered 8-inch square pan and cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: meat balls for hot hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
In a skillet, brown meat balls in shortening.
Take meat balls out of skillet and pour out fat.
In same skillet, heat chili and grape jelly until all of jelly is dissolved.
Add meat balls and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: basil and tomato salad
directions: Marinate tomatoes in mixture of 1 tablespoon basil, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper for 4 hours.
Stir tomatoes once or twice and baste with marinade.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground meat, pepper and onion; then drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes. Serve on sandwich bun.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss pot roast
directions: Brown roast in	oil
in
12-inch Dutch oven.
Add mushrooms, onions and spices.	Place
lid
on	oven and bake for 1 hour with 6 coals below
and	12 coals above.
At the end of 1 hour add the apple juice and turn meat.	Bake for an additional 2 1/2
hours. When
done	remove	everything from the oven except the juice. Pour
milk into juice.
Mix flour and water and stir into Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling (3 to 5 minutes) to thicken gravy.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Put berries in a pan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil. Mash berries and strain thorough cheesecloth.
Use 3 1/2 cups juice to 1 package of Sure-Jell.
Bring to a rapid boil; add sugar and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour into jelly glasses and seal.

title: zucchini chow chow
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, peppers and salt.
Let stand overnight, covered.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
Be sure to squeeze to get surplus water out.

title: tammy wynette sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar thoroughly; add eggs. Blend in remaining ingredients, one at a time, beating thoroughly. Bake in a tube pan at 325°
approximately 1 hour.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Combine above ingredients to form meatballs.

title: rolled oats cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream brown sugar, white sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and oat mixture.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Pour into greased cake loaf pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Blend until well mixed; add pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
If pie starts to get too brown before it's done, make a tent by folding foil and spreading it over the pie.
This will prevent crust and pecans from burning.

title: bebop broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour 3/4 of melted oleo into bowl of ingredients, leaving some oleo in pan.
Mix well.
Pour into the 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: roasting peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise and remove the seeds.
Place pepper halves, cut side down, on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until skin is bubbly and brown.
Place the peppers in a paper bag.
Seal and let stand for 20 to 30 minutes or until peppers are cooled.
Pull off skin slowly.
Slice peppers and mix with olive oil and crushed garlic.
Refrigerate.

title: orange bread
directions: Peel orange down to fruit.
Cut into strips.
Boil 10 minutes with 1 teaspoon soda.
Rinse well.
Cook peeling with 1 cup sugar and orange juice; cook pretty low, but not dry.
Chop.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice the potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Grease a 2-quart casserole and alternate layers of sweet potatoes and apples, topping each layer of apples with the butter, salt, brown sugar and a sprinkling of cinnamon or mace.
Pour the apple juice or water over the top layer and bake for 1 hour until the apples are tender and the top is lightly browned.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and bananas together.
Add brown sugar and butter.
Add salt and cinnamon.
Whip all ingredients together; stir in nuts.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour marinade
directions: This is the marinade for sweet and sour pork, but it is excellent on chicken too, especially when cooked on the grill.

title: pudding tart
directions: Mix crackers, margarine and butter together and press 1/2 mixture into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese (room temperature) and 2/3 cup powdered sugar until soft and creamy (easy to spread).
Fold in 1/2 of the 9 ounces of Cool Whip. Spread mixture over crust.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: In a double boiler over medium heat, cook and stir eggs, sugar and vinegar until mixture is thickened and reaches 160°. Remove from heat. Stir in butter. Cool.

title: supper salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water, salt and onion together and chill until slightly
thickened.
Stir	rest
of
ingredients
into cooled gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve plain or on a lettuce leaf.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, cocoa, butter and milk together.
Stir until it starts to boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and put in pan of cold water to cool.
Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, cut and serve.

title: quick banana muffins
directions: Melt margarine; beat in eggs and sugar.
Mash bananas and add to egg mixture.
Add flour and baking soda and stir.
Pour into cupcake papers.
Makes a dozen or a few more depending on size of bananas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Super moist and only 10 minutes to stir up and have in oven.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook beef on high until browned.
Add spaghetti sauce and water to beef.
Combine Ricotta cheese and egg.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce, then a layer of uncooked noodles, egg mixture and Mozzarella cheese alternately in a rectangular microwave dish. Repeat to form two layers.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes, then on 50% power for 30 to 32 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in baking dish; stir in soup and cheese. Add milk and mayonnaise.
Add egg gradually until well blended. Pour over broccoli and sprinkle bread crumbs over the top.
Cover with foil for half of the baking time.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and pat dry. In large roasting pan, melt butter and oil over moderate heat. Add herbs and spices and mix well. Add potatoes and roll them in mixture to coat. Bake about 40 minutes, until potatoes are tender, basting occasionally.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in baking dish, breast side up.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size of chicken.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cheeses with electric mixer.
Add the Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Chill 8 hours.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecan nuts.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add celery, green pepper and onion; saute until tender.
Add tomato juice, salt, basil and Tabasco; bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly with spoon.
Refrigerate until firm enough to form a ball.
Roll in 1 cup of pecans.

title: chewy nut squares
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until fine crumbs form.
Put in 8-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove.
Mix remaining flour and sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour over crusts.
Bake 30 minutes or until top is set.
Cool.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: slush
directions: Put in tupperware and freeze at least 24 hours.
Fill glass with slush and 7-up. Mix.
Fits in gallon buckets doubled.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. To serve, fill 1/2 full with powdered mix and add hot water.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, apricot nectar, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Use sheet cake pan.

title: reduced fat poke cake
directions: Poke holes with fork in cake in 1/2-inch intervals (cooled cake).
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and stir.
Pour gelatin over cake.
Chill cake in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours.
Frost cake with Cool Whip.
Can mix fresh strawberries or bananas in with Cool Whip.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan. Makes 18 servings.

title: cream of broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onions and broccoli in 2 1/2 quart covered pan until tender.
Blend cottage cheese in blender until very smooth. Slowly
add milk and blend.
Add soup and blend, then add
to cooked undrained vegetables.
Heat about 3 minutes, do not boil. Add salt and pepper to taste and serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.
Save broth for later use. Melt margarine in medium or large size baking dish. Add chicken and vegetables, spreading over bottom of dish.
Mix soup and broth well.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Do not stir.
Blend flour and milk in blender.
Pour gently over mixture in dish.
Do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, mayonnaise, catsup, Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Add onion and shrimp, then salt and pepper.
This is better, if refrigerated overnight.
It keeps a long time in the refrigerator.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients.
Put in covered casserole. Bake 1 hour in a medium oven.

title: royal kona coffee cheese cake
directions: Mix together and spread on the bottom of a pie pan.
Press firmly. Bake at 375°.
Cool.

title: pineapple cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and roll in pecans.

title: chicken wrap-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions and seasoning in small bowl. Roll mixture into 6 balls.
Place balls in center of flattened chicken breasts.
Fold chicken around ball.
Wrap two bacon strips around each chicken breast, securing with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: yam cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham crackers and melted margarine, mixing well.
Press into bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all and mix.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables. Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Mix with whipping cream.
Form around each cherry.
Place on waxed paper on cookie sheet and freeze.
Melt together the chocolate chips and wax in a double boiler.
Dip each cherry into chocolate with a toothpick.
If you get the cherries with the stem still on, you can dip them with it.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil
chicken
until
done.
Save broth and cooked spaghetti noodles
in
it.
Drain
noodles
and
add 1/2 stick of butter, 1 can mushroom soup, small can of Carnation milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Add chicken pieces, cut into bite size pieces.
Can add olives, if you like.
Heat in 325° oven for 30 minutes, longer if you have refrigerated it.
This recipe improves with age.
Serves 15 people.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave just until it's soft enough to spread with a knife.
Place 1 fudge strip cookie flat on table; spread melted chocolate around the center of it.
Place pinwheel cookie on it's edge in center of 1st cookie.

Take the 2nd fudge strip cookie; spread chocolate on half of it and stick it to the back of the pinwheel cookie so that it looks like tail feathers. Take candy corn and put chocolate on the edge of it and stick it in the top center of the pinwheel cookie to make it look like a beak.

title: baked fish
directions: Line pan with foil.
Rub butter or margarine on foil.
Season both sides of fish with salt, pepper and lemon pepper if desired. Put fish on foil.
Slice lemon, green onions, garlic and onion over fish.
Seal and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.
If necessary, bake about 5 minutes more.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pecans to jello mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry cool whip salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add boiling water to reserved syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange peel.
Chill until partially set (consistency of unbeaten egg white).
Fold in orange sections and pineapple. Cool cream until soft peaks form; fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold and serve.

title: chilly carrots
directions: Combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Add green pepper and onions.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate.
Keeps very well.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and milk and put on cookie sheet.
Press down until 1 inch thick.
Chill in freezer 1 hour. Cut into pieces.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Place in roaster and pour in mushroom soup diluted with milk.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Dip tortillas in chicken broth and place on bottom of a buttered casserole dish 13 x 18 inches.
Spread the chicken pieces on top of tortillas.
Mix together 1/2 c. chicken broth, Cream of Chicken soup, Cream of Mushroom soup, heat slightly.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Pour Rotel tomatoes over this.
Spread pimentoes over.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: basic salsa
directions: Empty tomatoes and juice in bowl.
Use wire whisk to break up or use food processor to mix.
Add all others.
Chill 2 hours. Refrigerate.

title: three bean salad
directions: Bring to a boil green pepper, onion, pimento, vinegar, oil, sugar and salt.
Cool and pour over beans.
Set for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Cook until marshmallows are melted.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Have cheese at room temperature and place in bowl; add hot mixture slowly to cheese, beating until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill, covered, with plastic wrap until partially set. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2-quart mold or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate, covered, until firm.
Delicious.

title: crisco white cake icing
directions: Put all ingredients together and beat except for coconut. The longer you beat, the creamier it will be.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, cocoa and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with fresh fruit or pound cake.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour pork and beans in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Add eggs, sugar, butter and buttermilk.
Add flour until mix is stiff enough to roll out.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in 325° oven until desired doneness.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, unless already coated. Spread pineapple on bottom of pan.
Layer cherries over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries.
Sprinkle nuts over mix. Layer sliced butter in rows over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
"Great warm or cold with vanilla ice cream."

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add mashed potatoes.

Add enough milk to make firm dough, but not too stiff. Roll out on floured cutting board, then cut with biscuit cutter. Place in greased biscuit pan and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until browned.

title: autumn scallop
