directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: chili
directions: Brown onions and garlic in a small amount of oil.
Add ground chuck and brown.
Add Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper; stir well.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Add beans the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: easy fudge cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients three times, after third sifting, sift into an ungreased cake pan.
Mix together all other ingredients and put on top of dry ingredients.
Stir, getting into corners.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: iron skillet chicken
directions: Mix ingredients well and soak chicken for 15 minutes.
Drain and pan-fry in hot iron skillet 8 minutes per side or until done. Chicken should be browned well on both sides.

title: tecie blairs lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolk, add Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and rind and stir; set aside.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and cream of tartar, beat until peaks are formed.
Fold into other mixture. Pour into baked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: eggnog rice pudding
directions: Heat eggnog over low heat.
Combine cornstarch and milk.
Pour into eggnog, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add raisins just before removing from heat.
Add salt and rum extract.
Fold in cooled rice.
Pour into individual dishes; chill.
Serve plain or with whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 4.

title: apple transparent pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna toss
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to directions; drain. In large skillet, brown ground beef with onion and garlic; drain. Stir in sauce and simmer 10 minutes or until heated through. Stir pasta into sauce.
Place 1/2 pasta mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Combine cottage cheese with parsley; evenly spread on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Place remaining mixture on top of cheese; cover with remaining Mozzarella. Sprinkle with Parmesan, if desired.
Cover; bake 20 to 25 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in long casserole dish. Salt and pepper chicken to taste and place on top of first mixture.
Pour butter over.
Sprinkle heavily with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cover for the first hour.

title: no bake crunchies
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter; stir to melt.
Remove from heat.
Add corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet or pour into pan.
Freeze or refrigerate for 5 minutes to eat in a hurry.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, well beaten, and then stir in bananas.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to make a smooth batter.
Dredge pork in batter.
Heat oil to 375° and deep-fry pork until golden brown. Drain, place in deep bowl and pour sweet and sour sauce over pork.
Serve hot.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix milk and vinegar together.
Set aside.
Cream margarine. Add eggs one at a time.
Then add sugar and vanilla; mix well. Then add dry ingredients together with sour milk mixture and mashed bananas.
Grease one 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and one 6-cup cake pan.
Pour batter in pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage squash special
directions: Cook sausage and onion until brown.
Drain.
Cook squash in small amount or water until tender.
Drain.
Mix sausage and squash with next 6 ingredients.
Fold eggs in carefully and place in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2 oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put can of cherry pie mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add undrained pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter on top. Add nuts if you like.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Combine the 3 ingredients; work in sausage and cheese well. Drop and shape.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops well; put salt and pepper on them.
Pour barbecue sauce into bowl.
Dip each chop into the sauce, then place in a deep baking dish.
Take remainder of sauce and add about 1/2 cup of water to it and mix.
Pour the mixture over the chops.
Take a piece of aluminum foil and place over top of the dish and put into oven and bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on desired tenderness.

title: homemade kraut
directions: Wash, core and shred cabbage; the finer the better.
Pack in a stone churn or glass jars.
Divide cabbage, put cabbage in first add 1/4 cup salt and use the dasher to pack until the juice covers the cabbage.
Repeat layers until the desired amount of kraut you want to make.
Cover and let set for 10 to 14 days, remove from crock, and rinse.
Heat and pack in jars.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well flour, salt and Crisco.
Mix liquids and add to flour mixture.
Refrigerate until cold.
Roll out and put in pan.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: rigatoni with zucchini and garlic
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and 1/4 cup of the white wine.
Simmer 20 minutes, adding white wine when needed to keep sauce from overthickening. Add zucchini and cook until desired doneness.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Parboil cabbage. Combine soup and salad dressing. Warm slightly. Melt margarine and spread over bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Add corn flakes. Next, add drained cabbage. Pour warm soup mixture over cabbage. Add cheese. Can crumble few more corn flakes on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party-style chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out French bread loaf; save removed bread to slice or cube and serve with salad or for making croutons.
Put salad into hollowed loaf.

title: lemon-baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine lemon juice, oil or butter, garlic, salt, and pepper.
Arrange chicken in a shallow casserole or baking dish.
Pour lemon and oil mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake until tender (approximately 40 minutes), basting occasionally.
Uncover casserole dish and bake 10 minutes longer to allow chicken to brown.
To serve, sprinkle with chopped parsley (optional).

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Mix boiling water with cranberry sauce and heat until blended. Heat to just boiling and pour over combined jellos.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Allow cake to cool.
Mix well the milk, cream cheese and pudding and spread over cooled cake.
Set cake in refrigerator for 15 minutes and mix the pineapple, Dream Whip and coconut and add to top of cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and place maraschino cherries on top.
Can be frozen.

title: un-fried french fries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals.
Slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° until cheese bubbles. Easy and very filling!

title: chiles rellenos
directions: Brush peppers with oil and, on a rack set on an electric burner at high heat or using a long-handled fork over an open flame, roast them, turning them for 5 minutes.
Transfer peppers to a bowl and cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Let peppers steam for 5 minutes.
Wearing rubber gloves, peel.
Make a lengthwise slit in side of each pepper from stem to tip.
Remove ribs and seed carefully, leaving stems intact.
Rinse the peppers gently; put them on paper towels to drain.
May also be roasted in oven.

title: perfect potatoes
directions: Stir soup and 1 stick oleo over medium heat until oleo is melted.
Add sour cream.
Stir in hash browns and pour into a baking pan.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top.
Pour 1 stick of melted oleo on top of crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: venison chop suey
directions: Boil until tender; thicken with cornstarch or flour.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Shred cabbage to make 2 quarts.
Boil for 10 minutes and drain.
In a saucepan, heat the other ingredients together until the cheese melts.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil together margarine, water and cocoa.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Then add eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla.
Pour into jelly roll pan (15 x 9 x 2-inch) and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost cake while warm with frosting.

title: vienna coffee break
directions: Combine 1/2 cup scalded milk, 1/4 cup shortening, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add compressed yeast, crumbled or active dry yeast, dissolved as directed on package.
Mix well. Blend in egg (slightly beaten).
Add sifted flour; mix well.
Knead on floured board for a few minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until double in bulk, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Roll out dough on floured board to a 12-inch square.
Combine cocoa, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over dough.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise in warm place until almost double in bulk (1 1/4 to 2 hours).
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while warm.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cut cabbage head in half and separate leaves.
Cook the cabbage leaves and sliced onion in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes or until wilted and tender.
Drain well.
Layer cabbage and onion mixture, cheese and soup 1/2 at a time in casserole dish.
Top with soft bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: "my" muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg, oil and walnuts or raisins.
Stir until evenly moist.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: play dough
directions: Place all ingredients in electric skillet, set on low.
Stir until "play dough" consistency.
Knead and play!

title: orange cooler
directions: Blend strawberries, 1 cup orange juice and honey in blender for 10 seconds.
Mix in pitcher with remaining orange and grape juice.
Serve in chilled glasses.
Garnish with mint sprig.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Mix the vanilla pudding and milk.
Mix the Cool Whip into the vanilla pudding; let set.
Cover bottom of cake pan with graham crackers.
Pour in the pudding/Cool Whip mixture.
Put more graham crackers on top and cover with chocolate frosting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla well. Blend all dry ingredients and stir into margarine mixture.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 1 1/4-inch balls and place 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake about 10 minutes; only until just beginning to brown. Cool on rack.
Store in tight container.
Cookie will stay soft and chewy.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Grease bottom of casserole and line with chipped beef.
Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 275° oven for 3 hours.
May top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Add tarragon to prepared white sauce.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/3 of the noodles, 1/2 the seafood, 1/3 each of the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses and the white sauce; repeat.
Top with remaining noodles, white sauce and cheeses.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with fork; pour cream of coconut and condensed milk over cake.
Let cake cool.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut flakes.

title: venison roast with sauce
directions: Combine tomato sauce, salt, pepper, onion, vinegar, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Place the venison on large sheet of heavy foil in baking dish.
Cover roast with sliced bacon.
Pour tomato mixture over roast.
Fold and seal the foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or until tender.
Check halfway through cooking.
Add a little more water if too dry to keep from burning.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients vigorously to make soft dough; knead.
Allow dough to rest about 5 minutes.
Top with favorite sauce (I use my own sauce).
Top the sauce with pepperoni, sliced low salt hot dogs, trail bologna, browned hamburg or your choice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella, Romano or your favorites.
It works well to mix.
Top with mushrooms, peppers, onions or other vegetables.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is well browned.
Makes one 14-inch pizza.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix and drop onto cookie sheet.
Put leftovers in refrigerator to use at later time.

title: sweet-sour kraut and chops
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, combine potato slices, onion and 1/4 cup water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 45 minutes.
While this is baking, in skillet, brown pork chops on both sides in hot oil.
In a bowl, combine sauerkraut, undrained pineapple and brown sugar.
Spoon this over potato mixture.
Place chops on top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, another 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and mash. Add other ingredients.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and thinly slice apples in large bowl. Sprinkle with juice, sugar and cinnamon. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pie crust and place other pie crust on top. Make slits on top.
Place in microwave oven for 10 minutes on High.

title: tasty hot chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and 1/2 cup water in a mixing bowl.
Add next 8 ingredients; mix well.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups of potato chips and eggs.
Place in a large casserole.
Top with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes at 400°, then 10 minutes at 350°.

title: orange pecandy
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and milk to boil.
Add orange juice and cook to 234° on candy thermometer.
Add peel and cook to 250°. Cool.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Store in airtight container.

title: chutney
directions: Chop vegetables size according to prefer.
I prefer small pieces.
Mix with other ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook ham bone in 1 1/2 quarts water about 1 hour.
Add all vegetables and cook until tender over low heat.
Add spaghetti and cool until done.
Remove meat from bone before serving.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool cake before icing.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except rice and heat until cheese is melted through.
Pour into large casserole.
Add rice. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: blender potato pancakes
directions: Blend and bake in frying pan.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple juice into 2-quart casserole.
Set pineapple chunks aside.
Blend vinegar, sugar, ketchup, cornstarch, soy sauce, garlic powder and cayenne into juice.
Stir in pork. Microwave at power level 7 for 9 to 12 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, stirring every 3 minutes.
Stir in onion, green pepper and carrots.
Cover and microwave at power level 7 for 6 to 9 minutes or until sauce thickens and becomes translucent and vegetables are tender and crisp, stirring every 3 minutes.
Stir in tomato and pineapple chunks.
Microwave uncovered at power level 7 for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with rice.

title: apricot tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons per cup and boiling water.

title: oven french fries 1(french fries without frying)
directions: Preheat oven to 475°. Peel (or leave peeling) potatoes and cut into long strips, about 1/2-inch square. Dry strips thoroughly on paper towels. Toss in a bowl with oil as if making a salad. When strips are thoroughly coated with oil, spread them in a single layer on a cookie sheet and place in the oven for 35 minutes. Turn strips periodically to brown on all sides.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Add sugar to berries; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix jello into berries and pour in the boiling water; stir well.
Add fruit, juice and nuts.
Chill all until set.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, oil, water and cocoa.
Mix flour and sugar; add eggs, vanilla, soda and buttermilk.
Pour on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix all but eggs in large mouth jar.
Add eggs. Let stand covered 3 to 6 days.

title: clam dip
directions: In a small microwave safe bowl, mix together cream cheese and clams.
Heat in microwave for 1 minute. Stir in garlic powder and pepper. Heat in microwave for another minute. Remove and stir. Transfer to small serving dish. This dish may be served hot or cold.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: real mexican chili
directions: Mix chili powder and flour.
Add the meat.
Fry a small piece of tallow in shortening.
When very hot, fry in the garlic and the onions until very clear.
Add meat mixture and stir constantly until well browned.
Add tomatoes and chillies.
Pour into meat mixture 1 1/2 quarts boiling water and simmer until done, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: guajillo chile salsa(the real thing - medium hot)
directions: Prepare tomato by pan roasting until blistered, black and soft. Prepare garlic by pan roasting until brown and soft, then peel.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken on bottom of pan. Combine soup, sour cream and broth.
Scatter mushrooms over chicken. Cover with soup mixture. Melt butter and combine with crushed crackers.
Toss over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barley salad with corn and peppers
directions: Put barley in bowl.
Cover with warm water and rub gently. Drain and repeat until water is clear.
Drain.
Boil 8 cups of water.
Add 2 teaspoons salt and barley and return to boil. Simmer covered until tender, about 30 minutes. Drain and rinse with cold water and drain well.

title: chicken mushroom risotto
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, add butter.
Cook chicken until brown.
Remove and set aside.
In same saucepan, add rest of ingredients, keep heat at medium.
Cook onion, carrot (or pepper) and rice until rice is brown, stirring constantly.
Add broth, soup and pepper, simmer on low.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add chicken, cook 15 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In mixer, blend eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add oil, vanilla, sour milk and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: norwegian bread
directions: Heat butter and milk until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water in mixing bowl. Add sugar, salt, raisins, cherries and egg.
Add butter and milk mixture; mix well.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Beat well after each addition.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Turn out on floured surface.
Toss lightly until dough is covered with flour and not too sticky.
Divide into 3 parts and place in 3 well-greased, 1 pound coffee cans.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust and chill.
Top with chocolate!

title: sweet sandwiches
directions: Butter thin slices of bread and spread fruit with any kind of jelly, jam or marmalade.

title: sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Warm potatoes.
Drain.
Cream together butter, eggs, sugar and milk.
Add dash of cinnamon.
Mix with potatoes and pour in baking dish and cook 20 minutes at 400°.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Combine brown sugar, marshmallows and margarine in saucepan. Cook until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour over popcorn in large bowl; mix lightly.
Shape into 20 balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 20 balls.

title: crab salad
directions: Place lettuce on plates. Make a pile of crab meat on top. Sprinkle with egg yolk and top with dressing.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Blend in milk, salad oil, poppy seed and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add gradually to batter mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into 2 large greased loaf pans or 5 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour for large loaves or 45 minutes for small loaves.

title: seven-up punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, cookies will appear moist (do not overbake) or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: baked scallops with cream
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, saute zucchini and carrots in margarine until crisp-tender, about 3 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle flour over vegetables; toss lightly to coat and cook 1 minute over medium heat.
Add whipping cream; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Mixture will be thick.
Add scallops, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in wine.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar and Jell-O; add water.
Cook until thick.
Cool until very thick.
Mix in peaches.
Pour into pie crust and pile higher.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding with mixer on slowest speed. Fold sour cream and 1/4 of the Cool Whip into the pudding mixture. Do this with a large mixing spoon.
Layer the bottom and sides of bowl with vanilla wafers.
Add sliced bananas on top of wafers, then a layer of pudding mixture.
Repeat until all is used.
Add remainder of Cool Whip to top, starting in the center and smooth to edge.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and serve with apple slices, strawberries, cantaloupe, etc.

title: quick punch
directions: Chill all ingredients well.
Add ginger ale a few minutes before serving.
Float a few strawberries in punch or make an ice ring with strawberries.

title: veggie sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together in skillet; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until veggies are cooked.
Serve on buns with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in flour and cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: crab bisque supreme(or "easy" cream of crab)
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cream of mushroom soup, asparagus, milk and cream.
Heat just to boiling.
Add crabmeat.
Heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sherry.
Stir in butter, dash of hot sauce and Old Bay seasoning.
Serve sprinkled with paprika and chopped parsley.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook and stir ground meat until browned; drain.
In ungreased 2-quart casserole, mix macaroni, beef and remaining ingredients, except potato chips. Cover and bake 40 minutes; sprinkle top with chips and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In large bowl stir ingredients together in order given.
Cover and refrigerate dough at least 12 hours, then place on lightly floured board.
Let rise 2 hours.
Roll out and cut.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugars, shortening, sour cream, eggs, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla into large mixing bowl.
Mix well, using a pastry blender.
Add flour, coconut and oatmeal, mixing well as before. Push through a cookie press, using the 3/4-inch tube.
Cut dough into 2-inch logs.
Roll in a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreos and reserve 1/4 cup for later.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with Oreos.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice 1/2 gallon of any flavor ice cream and place over the cookie crumbs.
Spread 1 can of prepared frosting over ice cream layer.
(You can soften this in microwave or in bowl of hot water to spread easier.)

title: toad in the hole
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch cubes; season with salt and pepper.
Place in a shallow baking dish, which has been well-greased.
Spread beef cubes apart so that batter will form between them.
Make a batter of remaining ingredients and pour over cubes, allowing some to leave their "heads" out.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° to 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: favorite pot roast
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven.
Brown roast on all sides.
Add the bay leaf, salt, pepper and thyme leaves.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 hours.
Will make its own juices.
After 3 hours, add your potatoes, carrots and onions and continue to cook over low heat for another hour.

title: italian chicken cutlets
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Combine bread crumbs and next 5 ingredients.
Dip chicken in eggs and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown, adding extra oil if necessary. Drain on paper towels.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Add water to make a gallon.
Add strawberries.
Makes 16 cups.

title: brownie pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and shortening in a mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes with an electric mixer.
Stir in nuts. Spread batter in a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve with ice cream and chocolate syrup.

title: myra's crab cakes
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in butter. Mix with other ingredients. Shape into patties. Crush crackers and dip patties
in crumbs. May fry in hot oil or bake in 400° oven.

title: snowy potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cook as for mashed potatoes.
Mash and add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Beat with mixer on high until creamy.
Stir in chives; spoon into a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: poor man's steak
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Pat mixture on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 6 squares.
Roll each square in flour and brown in large skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan; cover with mushroom soup.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 425°.
Pour the apple pie filling into the unbaked pie shell.
Combine the pumpkin, molasses and melted margarine; blend well.
Combine milk and eggs; stir into the pumpkin mixture.
Pour over the apple pie filling.
Put the pie on the preheated cookie sheet in the oven.
To keep from spilling, add the last of the pumpkin mixture after the pie be full of brim. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes and top with whipped cream.

title: twinkle cake
directions: Place twinkies in a 13 X 9 dish and pour pineapple, including juice, over twinkies. Slice a layer of bananas over the pineapple. Mix the instant pudding and pour over bananas. Top with cool whip. You can add nuts and cherries.

title: hamburger casserole florentine
directions: Brown beef (leave in large chunks), onion, mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add defrosted spinach to beef mixture.
Mix soup, sour cream and cooked rice or pasta together; add to hamburger mixture.
Put entire mixture in casserole dish.
Layer Jack cheese on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, until hot and cheese is melted.
Enjoy!

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs just to mix (a good foam).
Gradually add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add scalded milk last.
(Do not let milk boil.) Pour into a deep pie pan and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 5 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake 25 minutes (until set).

title: black cherry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in half of the water required.
Use the juice from pineapple and cherries for the rest.
Pour half the Jell-O into mold and let it set until firm.
Add the other ingredients and rest of Jell-O.
Let it set until firm.
Serve as desired.

title: chicken napoli
directions: Place chicken and veggies in 4-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Add tomatoes, garlic powder, bouillon, Mrs. Dash and water.
Sprinkle with dill.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir after 1 hour.
The flavor continues to develop as the casserole stands.
Serves 6.

title: marbled cheesecake deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease pan or casserole dish.
Mix ingredients.
Save some grated cheese for top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lo-cal punch
directions: Pour all ingredients over sherbet. Serve.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll very thin.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough according to directions.
Don't worry about allowing to rise. Grease countertop.
Flatten dough into a 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Dot pepperoni and cover area. Add mushrooms and cheese. Begin at short end and roll, flattening out as you roll.
Pinch off ends. Bake on greased sheet 30 minutes at 350°. Allow to cool and slice into finger size pieces.

title: german chocolate delight
directions: Bake cake mix according to box directions for a 13 x 9 pan. Remove cake from oven and poke holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon while cake is still hot. Pour caramel syrup over cake. Top with crushed pecans and sweetened milk onto cake making sure filling gets in holes. Let cool. Top with Cool Whip and crushed Skor bars sprinkled over Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut patties
directions: Put sugar, Karo and water in pan; bring to boil.
Add peanuts and coloring.
Cook to hard ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla, salt and margarine.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into 4 buttered pans.
Let cool 1 hour.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: *Remove 1/2 cup for garnish.

title: penny carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and cool in ice water.
Add onion and pepper.
For dressing, mix tomato soup, salt oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt. Blend and beat well the dressing ingredients.
Pour over carrots, onion and peppers.
Mix and marinate for one day.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add prunes.
Add sour milk with dry ingredients.
Bake in large cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Very good and moist.
May use caramel frosting or cream cheese frosting.

title: grandma's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
In large bowl, mix sugar and margarine until fluffy, about 10 minutes.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Mix well on medium speed.
Be sure to scrape bowl while mixing, but please stop mixer before you do this. Pour into pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups of hot water.
Mix with sugar.
Let stand.
Grind cranberries and fix fruit.

title: caesar salad
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients in blender.
Cut romaine lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Add croutons!
Add dressing at time of serving (too soon, too soggy).

title: delicious lamb stew
directions: In a large pot with cover, brown meat on all sides in oil. Add onion, garlic and bay leaves while lamb is browning.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes; simmer 30 minutes longer.
Add green beans; continue to simmer while preparing to thicken gravy.
Blend flour and cold water; pour slowly into stew, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer, if needed, to achieve desired consistency.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kentucky fruitcake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Cool and drain, reserving liquid in a large mixing bowl. Set liquid and raisins aside.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and marshmallows.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, add apples, celery and walnuts.
Toss with sour cream and serve.

title: sausage parmesan(from leftover spaghetti sauce)
directions: Cook rope of sausage; when done, cut in 4 pieces the size of sub rolls.
Put sausage in roll; spoon spaghetti sauce over sausage and cover with pizza sauce.
Lightly sprinkle oregano over cheese and bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: basic french
directions: In a large cruet or bottle, combine first 6 ingredients, then shake.
Add catsup and vinegar.
Shake vigorously, then add oil and shake vigorously.
Chill before using.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll croissant rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 13 minutes, until light and brown.
Cool.

title: aunt gert's barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter, and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar and syrup or honey.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and soda.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork dipped in sugar to make crosshatching.
Bake at 375° for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs and blend well.
Sift and add flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and milk.
Mix well.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Place on baking sheet pan. Melt cheese and margarine together.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake as if you were baking biscuits.
Makes 40 biscuits.
Serve hot.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat the egg yolks until light, then beat in sugar until the mixture is thick.
Stir in milk and rum.
Chill for 3 hours, then pour into a punch bowl and fold in stiffly whipped cream.
Chill for 1 hour, then dust with nutmeg before serving.
Serves 24.

title: easy cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Cool-Whip, milk, and lemon juice until very creamy.
Split mixture into the two pie shells and chill if not still somewhat firm.
Once filling is firm, pour your favorite fruit topping over them and chill again before serving.
One can will cover both pies.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil until vegetables are tender.
Drain, reserving broth.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle in flour to make sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add cheeses, stirring until smooth.
Pour vegetable broth back in sauce, stirring.
Add vegetables.
Allow time for flavors to blend. Serve.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, corn syrup, melted butter, vanilla and pecans.
Mix slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour in oven at 350° until knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.
Cool.
Pie is set more for cutting when cool.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add next 4 seasonings.
Add next 6 cans of ingredients.
Simmer.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and oil.	Add well beaten eggs; add vinegar. Add
flour,
soda,	salt
and cocoa, then food coloring. Add milk last.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: plain rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and let stand 15 minutes.
Fill unbaked crust and dot with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a large skillet, saute garlic in olive oil and add the onions and peppers. Cook for 2-3 minutes. Add cumin, chili powder and add juice from the tomatoes. Simmer over low heat.

title: cheese ravioli in primavera sauce
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions; drain and keep warm.
In medium skillet, heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add carrots; saute for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms and zucchini; saute for 2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, lemon juice, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over ravioli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cream wheat corn "bread"
directions: Mix ingredients well. Bake until golden brown. This bread is good for people with stomach trouble.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour peaches in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of peaches.
Place pats of margarine on top of cake mix.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/8 teaspoon salt until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Continue beating, adding 1 cup sugar gradually until very stiff.
Spread a 1-inch layer in bottom of a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Pile remaining egg whites evenly around the sides of pan.
Bake very slowly (250°) for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until peas are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; lightly stir in soup, half of onions and black pepper.
Put into casserole and heat in 350° oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining onions over top and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Can use onion rings and put buttered bread crumbs on top.

title: donna's carrot souffle
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add butter and blend well. Add the eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm.
Need to double to serve 8.

title: sour milk pudding
directions: Bake 20 minutes and serve with sour sauce.

title: dreamsicle cookie mix
directions: For Jar:
Combine flour, soda and powder.
In 1 quart wide-mouth jar, layer drink mix, sugar, vanilla chips and flour. Mix pressing each layer firmly.
Attach recipe card with baking instructions.

title: tijuana meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper, carrot, onion and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack in 2-quart loaf baking dish.
Mix catsup, brown sugar, honey and mustard; spread mixture on meat loaf.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, vegetable oil and water.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, raisins, and nuts. Pour batter into 3 buttered pans and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: devil's food pound cake
directions: Blend all
ingredients
and
beat
minutes at medium speed. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake in 350° preheated
oven for 50 to 60 minutes until center springs back
at light touch.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Thaw and drain spinach and set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Fold in spinach.
Place in a greased 8-inch pie pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Combine pasta and vegetables; toss well.
Mix Italian dressing and Good Seasons powder together.
Pour over pasta/vegetable mix. Sprinkle cheese over salad.
Toss well and chill.

title: chicken taco
directions: Saute onion and chilies in butter and flour.
Add tomato juice and cheese chunks, then add half and half cream.
When cheese is melted, add chicken.
Pour over chips.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: santa's thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Form 1 inch balls and roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press centers with thumb and fill with preserves.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower, leaving whole.
Drain well.
Place in a shallow pan (or ovenproof serving bowl) and frost with mixture of mayonnaise and mustard.
Sprinkle on the cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb juice
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb into small pieces.
Do not peel.
Place in a large kettle and add enough water so you can see it through rhubarb pieces but do not cover rhubarb.
Cook until mushy. Strain through cheesecloth.
Measure juice: Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups pineapple juice per quart of rhubarb juice. Reheat, bringing to boiling point.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Chill before serving.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 4 small layers at 325°.
Ice when cool.

title: granny buns
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Cover; let stand in a warm place 15 minutes.
Scald milk, then cool to warm.
Add milk, 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 teaspoons salt, 2 cups flour and 3 tablespoons shortening to yeast mixture.
Beat 2 minutes with a mixer.
Gradually stir in about 3 1/2 cups flour to make a very stiff dough.
Roll out dough on a floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness; fold in half.
Roll and fold 4 more times.
Divide in half.
Cover with bowl; let rest 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookie bar
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar; add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats.
Press half of mixture in 9 x 9-inch pan. Spread with your favorite jam.
Place remaining dough on top and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery about 8 minutes in slightly salted water.
Slice water chestnuts.
Mix all together in 1 quart casserole.
Toss 1/2 cup soft bread crumbs with 1/4 cup chopped almonds and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Crush crackers; mix with butter and sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Serve over rice.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cover chicken with 4 cups water; bring to a boil.
Cook covered for 1 hour or until tender.
Cook chicken; remove meat from bones, reserving broth and cut into bite-size pieces.
Dice bacon and cook in kettle.
Remove bacon.
Add beef, cut into 3/4-inch cubes, and onion; brown in fat remaining in kettle.
Add bacon, chicken broth, salt, paprika and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining vegetables and chicken and simmer for about 30 minutes longer.
Season to taste and thicken slightly with flour and water paste.

title: sugar-free lemon cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Bring water to a boil and add to gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add milk to pudding mix and blend.
Add dissolved gelatin to cream cheese and pudding mix. Beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into prepared graham cracker pie crust.
Put light Cool Whip on top when pie is set.

title: old-fashion peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together.
Cut in shortening and peanut butter with pastry blender.
Stir in syrup and milk.
Shape into logs; chill overnight.
Cut 1/4-inch pieces of dough.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk over medium heat stirring constantly, just until marshmallows are melted.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Stir in liqueurs.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold marshmallow mixture into whipped cream; fold in food color.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with grated semi-sweet chocolate if desired.
Refrigerate until set; at least 3 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan. Pour crushed pineapple over pie filling.
Over this, add cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top of cake mix, then add oleo, thinly sliced, to cover top completely.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear 1 layer of cake in hunks and put in bottom of pan or bowl. Pour 1 instant vanilla pudding over cake hunks.
Spread 1 can pineapple (juice and all) over pudding.
Pour 1 can pie filling over pineapple.
Spread 1 container Cool Whip over pie filling. Sprinkle pecans over pie filling.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans. Repeat all steps.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 10-inch pan.
Cook meat and onions; stir in seasoning mix, cook to blend.
Spread in pie pan. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes, then top with tomatoes and cheese. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.

title: kathy's pineapple casserole
directions: This is not a dessert.
It is delicious served with pork, especially ham.

title: good punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: easy chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: chocolate candy cake
directions: Cook
water
and cocoa until thick.
Add shortening and sugar; mix well.
Cool and add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the
dry ingredients
and
add alternately with sour milk. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baby wipes
directions: Using a good sharp knife, cut the roll of paper towels in half.
Remove the cardboard center and place half roll of paper towels in Rubbermaid container.
Mix together water, shampoo and oil; pour over the towels.
Cover with lid and let set about 24 hours so that liquid mixture can penetrate through.
These are wonderful to keep in the car for cleaning up dirty faces and hands after meals on the go.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add eggs and margarine.
Mix; add chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Mix all well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Boil crushed pineapple in juice.
Empty into cool bowl.
Add Jell-O and cool to room temperature.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook stew
beef
in
pressure cooker for 30 minutes. In one pan, cook potatoes, cabbage, onion and celery.
In a large stock pot,
empty
both cans of tomatoes. Cut up the tomatoes. Add all the
other	canned	goods and simmer. Cut up jalapeno peppers and add
to vegetables. Add potato mixture when done. When stew beef is	done, separate meat from fat.
Add meat to vegetables.	Also add
juice	in which meat was cooked to add flavor.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken and bone.
Line baking dish with part of chips. Add chicken, onion, pepper and cheese.
Sprinkle with garlic salt. Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugarless health cookies
directions: Place raisins and dried fruit in small saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool for 3 minutes.
Beat in oil, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in sugar substitute and vanilla.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes. Pour over tomatoes. Chill well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed in a large mixing bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into a decorative serving bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with aluminum foil and pour oil in.
Put in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place chicken in pan, meaty side down.
Mix salt, oregano and paprika and sprinkle half on chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°. Remove from oven; turn chicken over.
Sprinkle with other half of remaining spices.
Bake 20 more minutes.
Remove from oven; spoon drippings over chicken.
Put sliced mushrooms on top of chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: oodles shrimp stir-fry
directions: Cook noodles in 3 cups boiling water for 3 minutes. Rinse with cold water and drain.
Heat oil in skillet.
Stir-fry onions until softened. Add carrots and mushrooms and stir-fry until onions are slightly brown (may also add slightly cooked broccoli).
Remove vegetables from skillet and stir-fry shrimp.
Replace veggies and add noodles, seasonings, lemon juice and 1/4 cup water.
Toss and heat through.
Serve with sesame seed and lemon wedges.

title: two minute fudge (microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass bowl, combine sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla (mixture will be too stiff to thoroughly blend in dry ingredients).
Place margarine in middle of bowl.
Microwave on 100% power for 2 minutes.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Blend in nuts or peanut butter.
Spread fudge in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let chill 1 hour in refrigerator or 30 minutes in freezer.
Keep refrigerated.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Place in punch bowl as follows:
one layer of cake, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 cherries, 1/2 fruit cocktail, 1/2 pineapple, coconut, nuts, 1 Cool Whip.
Repeat.

title: ham fingers
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, ham and Swiss cheese.
Spread margarine on bread (10 slices). Then spread on ham mixture.
Put together for sandwiches.
Cut into 3-inch fingers.
Chill.
Makes 30 fingers.

title: sweet dream salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice well together.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Drain the fruits.
Add to Cool Whip mixture. Chill.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Blend in water, stirring until dry ingredients are dissolved.
Add milk and bring to boil, stirring often.
Boil for 3 to 4 minutes until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Serve hot over ice cream or topping for cake.
Makes 1 cup.

title: kibbee
directions: Lightly oil bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wash burghul several times and soak for 10 minutes in cold water.
Add seasoning and onion to beef.
Drain burghul and mix thoroughly with meat mixture.
Grind mixture once or twice.
Knead well with ice cold water until mixture is soft.
Divide mixture in half, moisten hands with cold water and spread mixture evenly on bottom. Sprinkle washed pine nuts on bottom layer.
Make top layer with remaining mixture.
Smooth top and cut into diamond shapes (diagonal cuts).
Slide knife around edge of pan working Kibbee away from pan.
Make small holes with finger (1 in center and 2 each near top and bottom of tray).
Drizzle 4 tablespoons oil on top of Kibbee and add 4 pats of butter or margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Broil until brown.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle cold water over top of Kibbee.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples; dice into small pieces and set aside.
Mix together the flour and shortening.
Add enough water to form a soft dough.
Divide dough into biscuit size sections.
Roll each section as flat as possible.
Put apples on flattened dough; fold each area of circle up, tucking at top to seal in apples.
Place these in a greased baking dish.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is lightly browned; drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mix with margarine, sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except peaches.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour in well-greased deep dish pie plate.
Pour peaches over mixture. Mix 1 (8 ounce) cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons peach juice.
Pour over peaches and mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon/sugar on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: egg and kidney bean salad
directions: Combine eggs, beans, celery, parsley and onions.
Blend the French dressing with the seasoning; stir into egg mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Makes 6 servings, 1/2 cup each, 125 calories per serving.

title: zesty roasted chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan for chicken breast. Place chicken in pan. Mix remaining ingredients and brush over chicken. Bake, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and juice of chicken is no longer pink.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in oil until yellow.
Add slowly a mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix the yeast and the hot water; set aside.
Melt the margarine, sugar and buttermilk.
Mix and add to yeast mixture. Add flour.
Spoon into greased muffin pan and allow to set 3 hours to rise.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray frying pan with Pam and brown chicken breasts. Set aside. In saucepan, heat soup, 3/4 of cheese and milk to hot. Roll up the breast with each crescent roll. Top with soup and cheese mixture. Place in baking dish. Put rest of cheese on top. Cook until crescent rolls are brown.

title: cheese and bacon muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly; stir in milk the 1/3 cup bacon fat and 1 cup shredded cheese.
Set aside.
Sift together the flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Stir into the egg mixture.
Crumble the fried bacon and add to mixture.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese-corn chowder
directions: Microwave butter, uncovered, in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish on Full power until melted, about 30 seconds.
Stir in onion. Microwave, uncovered, on Full power until tender, about 2 minutes. Remove from dish; reserve.
Combine corn muffin mix and caraway seed.
Prepare according to package directions.
Spread batter in same buttered baking dish.
Spread reserved onion over top.

title: ranch style biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.
Mixture can be stored in refrigerator for several days.
Grease pan before cooking.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Chill and serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables. Yield: 3 cups.

title: my favorite coconut pie
directions: Melt oleo over low heat; stir in sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk. Blend well. Cook slowly until thick. Immediately stir in coconut and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue made from the egg whites. Sprinkle with coconut and brown in oven.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Foil line an 8-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 cup walnuts evenly; set aside.
In heavy pan, combine marshmallow, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch morsels; stir until morsels melt. Stir in orange and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: helen corbitt's poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir thoroughly.
Put in food processor.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly, until thick.
Stir in poppy seed.
Store in a cool place, but do not let freeze.
Serve on fresh fruit.
Makes 1 quart.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: lois knight's recipe for raisin cookies
directions: Bring water and raisins to boil.
Let boil briskly for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in baking soda. Let stand.

title: kettle gravy
directions: Place meat on warm platter; keep warm while preparing gravy. Skim excess fat from meat broth; store fat for future use in seasoning vegetables.
Measure broth; pour amount desired into pan.
Shake water and flour in covered jar (for a smooth mixture, it is important to put water in jar first, then the flour).
Stir flour mixture slowly into broth; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
If desired, add a few drops of bottled brown bouquet sauce.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients for 8 minutes.
Pour into round greased cake pan (I use angel food pan).
Mix together the sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top and swirl through cake with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (my oven).
After first cake, you may have to adjust baking time to fit your oven.
Set timer! Do not open oven while baking!
(It will fall if you do, but will still taste good.)

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Slice cookie roll as if to bake cookies, place in miniature muffin tin.
Use thumb to indent, place a Reese's cup in indention.
Bake by direction on cookie roll.
Let cool completely in pan before removing.
Yields approximately 24 cookies.

title: belgium salad
directions: Mix all together the green beans, corn, peas, green pepper, onion, celery and pimentos.
Set aside.

title: egg and sausage strata
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Layer a greased shallow baking dish with bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: Butter and grease 8 x 8 pan. Using a 3 qt. saucepan, mix sugar, milk, syrup, pumpkin and salt. Bring to a boil stirring constantly; reduce heat to medium and continue boiling--do not stir.

title: chinese chews
directions: Place the chocolate and butterscotch chips in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 minutes by microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper-lined tray.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: grandma's coleslaw 'n' dressing(in honor of hasty grand slam)
directions: Shred cabbage (coarsely); it will make 4 to 5 cups.
Shred carrot.
Combine both in a large bowl.
Remove seeds and stems from green pepper (chop or dice), and add to the cabbage-carrot mixture.
Add celery seed.
Combine well.
Pour chilled coleslaw dressing (about 1/2 cup) over the cabbage mixture and mix well.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown meat with oil in large pan.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour in large dish and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or simmer in large pan on top of stove for 30 minutes.

title: pizza dolce-easter
directions: Line bottom of 2 (10-inch) pie pans with crust.
Blend all other ingredients; add to pie pans.
Add top crust.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: carolina apple cake
directions: Mix together flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add in order given:
corn oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, lemon juice, sliced apples and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (lightly greased and floured).
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
While still warm, glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of 1 1/2 lemons.

title: cabbage rollsroswell, new mexico
directions: Roast and peel 10-12 green chilies and stuff with strips of colby or cheddar cheese, leaving stems on.
Dip and fry in batter.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine all juices and punch.
Chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale.
Add ice ring, cubes or frozen sherbet ring as desired.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and heat.

Lay shells in baking dish. Fill with chicken mixture (reserving a little to pour on top) and fold shells once. Pour the reserved chicken mixture on top. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pollo con arroz(chicken and rice)
directions: Boil chicken two hours or until meat is falling off bone. Remove meat from bone.
Return to liquid with rice and boil until rice is done.
Serve in large bowl.
Serves 6.

title: oven baked cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease your skillet and put it in oven to get it hot, then pour your cornbread mix into skillet and let it cook for 30 minutes at 425° or until done.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomatoes and refried beans.
Cook for 20 minutes on medium heat.
In large, hot frypan, saute peppers, onions and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add vegetables, beans and spices.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
If too thick, add reserved tomato juice.

title: beth's honey chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan you plan to cook chicken in.
Combine other ingredients.
Roll chicken in this mixture and place in pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: green chile stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of olive oil. Sprinkle flour over meat. Add onions and cook until tender. Add chiles, garlic, broth, tomatoes, hominy, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer slowly until meat is tender.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and salt in a double boiler.
Add eggs and mix well.
Let cool slightly and add nuts and marshmallows.
Roll in wax paper and chill in refrigerator.
Makes 2 rolls.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips that have been allowed to reach room temperature and chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top, if desired. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: carrot salad with nuts and raisins
directions: Coarsely grate carrots.
Mix carrots with raisins, peanuts, salt and pepper.
Blend lemon rind, juice and sour cream.
Pour over carrot mixture and toss thoroughly.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and mushrooms. Stir.
Add 1/2 of the cheese.
Add sugar, salt and pepper to taste (sometimes I use seasoned salt).
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake one hour at 350° or until brown on top.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put everything in pot and bring to a boil.
After it starts to boil, reduce to simmer and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Blend all ingredients, except hash browns, together well.
Mix creamed mixture into hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in medium size saucepan.
Add onion and sugar. Cook and stir 5 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Add bouillon, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Bake cake 25 minutes at 350°.
Put topping on cake and bake 15 minutes more at 400°.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Knead well.
Chill at least 6 hours or overnight.
Roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with various shapes of cookie cutters. Decorate with frosting.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and chill.
Just before serving add ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: grandma's banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas, mixing just until blended.
Combine pecans in 1 teaspoon flour; stir into batter. Bake at 350° in Bundt pan for 40 to 45 minutes or loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into small square pieces.
Deep fry with a milk, egg and flour batter.
Set aside.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Stir together sugar, egg and shortening.
Add baking soda and cold water; stir.
Then add flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Stir, then add raisins, apples and nut meat if desired. Mix well; pour into pan (any size).
Bake at 360° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Let cool 10 minutes, then spread with margarine and sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: stuff
directions: Brown ground beef and add garlic powder and salt to taste. Add onion, peppers and chili powder.
Cook until tender.
Stir in rice and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly and top with cheddar cheese.
Serve with corn chips and refried beans.

title: party spinach dip
directions: Process cottage cheese until smooth.
Press spinach between paper towel until barely moist.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients to cheese mixture.
Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate about 3 hours.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: amaretti(cookies)
directions: In a small bowl, very lightly beat egg white, Amaretto and almond extract together.
In a large bowl, put almonds and sugar and mix well.
Put egg white mixture in and mix to form paste. Shape mixture into 36 equal size balls and put on cookie sheets (coated with grease and wax paper).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until just lightly brown.
Remove cookies from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool cookies on baking sheets.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir beef and onion over
medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over ground beef. Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake another 5 to 8 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.

title: cream of avocado soup
directions: Use a large blender to make this cold soup.
Avocados may be 2 large or 3 small.
Cut lengthwise with a chopping knife to seed. Twist to separate halves.
Remove seeds (one method is to embed knife into seed firmly and twist).
With a large spoon, scoop out meat and coarsely chop.
Add to blender.
Puree.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Separate into halves.
To each half, add 1 cup of milk, blend.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve cold in chilled soup bowls.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy black forest cherry tort
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake according to directions on package.
Line bottom of pan with single layer of marshmallows.
Pour cake mix on top.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Marshmallows will rise to top.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni and hamburger separately.
Put together in 3-quart saucepan.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and any other optional ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Serve with rolls.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Stir in flour and milk. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Drop from tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.
(May freeze.)

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Mix 1 stick butter melted with Pepperidge Farm herb mix and add on top. Cook until it bubbles.

title: ron's roast
directions: Cut several slits in 1 side of roast.
Place 1 green onion and small piece of garlic clove in each slit.
Cut onion off even with roast.
Turn over and repeat on other side (3 to 4 slits is good).

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cube.
Mix butter and cheese.
Add to potatoes.
Stir in sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (greased). Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Note:
Can keep small amount of Cool Whip for topping.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix. Spread mixture on a round platter.
Spread on diced onion, tomatoes, cheese and shredded lettuce. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Crunch up noodles into small pieces.
Put noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds on cookie sheet and toast until golden brown. Mix or shake canola oil, sugar, vinegar and seasoning pack from Ramen noodles.

title: foiled zucchini
directions: Place sliced zucchini on double strength foil, one zucchini for each person.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Parmesan.
Add dab of margarine and 1 tablespoon water.
Wrap carefully.
Cook on coals about 15 minutes.

title: raw apple bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening, 1 cup of sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour mixture.
Add apples, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine dressing, vinegar and curry powder; add to rice mixture and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 4 servings.
Contains 95 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients, except additional crumbs and butter, mixing with a fork until blended.
Shape into 9 patties, using 1/4 cup for each.
(Lay on waxed paper.)
Flatten slightly.
Dip into additional crumbs.
Melt butter in frypan and add patties.
Brown 5 minutes on each side, adding more butter if necessary.

title: crustless coconut-pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs for 1 minute. Add flour, salt and sugar; beat.
Add melted butter and beat. Add vanilla, pecans and coconut. Pour into greased dish and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: imitation lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic.
Mix in jar of spaghetti sauce. In the meantime, cook sea shell macaroni until done; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mixture to pasta.
Add cheeses; mix.
Can be put in crock-pot.

title: baked catfish parmesan
directions: Dip or brush fish with butter.
Roll in a mixture of bread crumbs or flour, cheese and lemon pepper.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of a glass and flatten cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate macaroon cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan on bottom only.
Mix following ingredients in small bowls and set aside:
beat egg white and 1/2 cup sugar until stiff, then stir in coconut, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In separate bowl, stir cocoa into hot coffee. Beat until stiff 3 egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar in another bowl. Mix baking soda in sour cream in separate bowl.
Now in large bowl, cream 1 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup shortening; add 3 egg yolks, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla and half of cocoa mixture.
Beat until light and creamy, about 4 minutes; add 2 cups flour, sour cream mixture and remaining cocoa mixture.
Blend well; fold in egg whites.
Pour in 1/3 batter; put half of coconut mixture on top. Cover with 1/2 remaining batter; top with remaining coconut mix and last with batter.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and 1 1/2 jars marshmallow cream. Add orange flavoring and mix.
Serve with any fruit you like (apples, bananas, chunk pineapple, etc.).

title: cheesy chili casserole
directions: Combine cheeses.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish layer cheese and chilies.
Combine eggs, flour and milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top casserole with half the tomato sauce or salsa.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Pass remaining sauce for topping.

title: ice cream cookie sandwich
directions: Line the bottom of a 9-inch round cake pan with aluminum foil. Spread ice cream in an even layer in pan.
Return to freezer until firm.
Run a knife around edge of pan to loosen ice cream. Remove from pan.
Wrap in foil and return to freezer.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together:
put in baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over all.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and drizzle over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glorified beef tips
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove bay leaves and serve on rice or noodles. Also good on bread as hot roast beef sandwiches.
Serves 4.

title: boneless pork spareribs with shanghai sauce
directions: In bowl, mix together all ingredients, except ribs.
Place ribs in large pan and pour mixture over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours, turning several times.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then uncover and continue to cook, while basting, until ribs are tender (1 hour more).

title: mom's chip beef gravy
directions: Melt butter or margarine and tear beef into bite-size pieces in skillet.
Sprinkle just enough flour to soak up butter or margarine.
Stir.
Pour in milk (about half of skillet).
Cook until bubbles and thickens.
Keep on low.

title: teacakes
directions: Mix sugar and eggs and pour the butter in.
Add the vanilla. Pour this mixture into the flour a little at a time.
Mix with your fingers.
Roll the dough thin and cut with a cookie cutter. Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 325° until brown.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour with cherries, pineapple, nuts and raisins. Toss to coat.
Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; set aside.
Soften margarine and beat in sugar. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well. Add flour mixture gradually.
Add milk.
Stir in fruit mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Yields 9 dozen.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix butter, sugar, baking powder, flour, salt and milk.
Pour fruit in center, then the mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350°.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Add to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form in balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Heat the cherries; drain. Heat the Brandy slightly and pour over the cherries. Add the Cointreau. Put a match to liquid and serve over ice cream while it burns.

title: creamy pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices in rows in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan; press to edges and corners.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla; mix at low speed until well blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Spread mixture over cookie base.
In a large bowl, combine 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, ginger, salt, cloves, pumpkin, milk and eggs; mix well.
Carefully pour pumpkin mixture over cream cheese layer.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool; refrigerate.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Using a mixer, beat the margarine, salt, baking powder and flour until crumbly.
These ingredients are the mix.
This will keep in the refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Prepare the mashed potatoes or bring leftover potatoes to room temperature.
Season to taste.
Beat egg yolks into mashed potatoes until well mixed.
Stir in the cheese, onion, green pepper and celery salt.
Salt to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook rice as directed on package; set aside.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning, tomatoes and chilies.
Mix well and cook over low heat until heated through.

title: fast and easy fruit dessert
directions: Drain peaches, pears and pineapple; cut into bite-size pieces. Mix in frozen strawberries.
Sprinkle dry pudding over top.
Do not stir.
Cover and let set overnight, all day or if you're in a big hurry, an hour will do.
Before serving, stir; add sliced bananas.
Eat and enjoy!

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until edges are lightly browned.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Cut roast into 1-inch cubes.
Mix onion soup, water and mushroom soup; pour over beef.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 300° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.
I rate recipes with stars, 4 stars being the highest.
This one is definitely 4 stars.

title: senior citizens cake(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Place fruit, margarine and water in saucepan and bring to a boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add egg whites, applesauce, vanilla and nuts to dry ingredients. Add fruit mixture to batter and bake at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Cake needs to be wrapped and kept refrigerated.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter dish.
Add milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Put in microwave oven until hot.
Take out and add rest of ingredients in dish. Bake in a 350° oven in pan of water for 1 hour or more.
Test with knife and if comes out clean it's done.

title: no calorie salad
directions: Combine milk and Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple, oranges and cocktail mix and add milk mixture.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in cherries.
Not necessary to refrigerate.

title: butter and almond flavored icing
directions: Combine ingredients in small mixing bowl and mix well.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Put into mold or roll and chill overnight.
Slice as thin as possible and bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: lazy chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cube meat. Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream of chicken soup and water; pour this over the chicken. Mix self-rising flour, milk and melted oleo; pour this over soup. Pour chicken broth over this and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel egg. Cut in half lengthwise.
