Remove egg yolks. Place egg whites in shallow container. Mash egg yolks with a fork, one at a time, until they are of a powdery consistency. Place yolks in a bowl and add the mayonnaise, vinegar and salt. Mix until light and fluffy.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture. Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Store in covered container in the refrigerator.
Make 12 deviled eggs, but recipe can be doubled.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground meat and onion together; drain fat. Combine meat mixture with undiluted tomato soup and green beans. Top with the leftover mashed potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add salt and baking powder to flour and sift.
Mix in flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla or any other flavoring to the batter.
Mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tested as done.

title: beef supper salad
directions: Combine in a bowl the mayonnaise, chili sauce, pickle relish and salt; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; pour dressing over mixture.
Toss lightly; chill.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Heat brown sugar, vinegar, turmeric and mustard.
Bring to boil; add vegetables.
Boil 10 minutes longer.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: bauernfruhstuck(german omelet)
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender and brown.
Add ham and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out all liquid.
Blend mayonnaise and sour cream; add soup mix and spinach.
Stir in water chestnuts. Cut the center out of the pumpernickel bread and fill the center with the dip.

title: prize chocolate cake
directions: Gradually add sugar to shortening; cream until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and cooled, melted chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost to your liking.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine
dry
cake mix, melted butter and eggs. Blend well.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Spoon pie filling evenly over batter.

title: leftover potatoes and onions
directions: Saute onion in small amount of vegetable oil in a skillet until tender and browned.
Add potatoes and stir until brown crust forms. Stir until heated through.

title: corn bread
directions: Break up bread into mixing bowl.
Pour milk over it and add egg, sugar and salt.
Beat until well blended and bread is disintegrated.
Add meal and baking powder; mix.
Add enough water to make batter thin.
Pour into heavily greased pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: knock you nakeds(a.k.a. turtle cake)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, pecans, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted butter.
Batter will be stiff.
Press 1/2 of the batter into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until almost done according to box directions.
Fry sausage.
Add butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add more milk if not moist enough.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: In a large pot, melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips over a low heat.
Stir in cereal until coated. Put sugar in a gallon sized Ziploc bag or a large container with a tight fitting lid.
Add cereal mixture; close tightly and shake gently to coat.
Store in airtight container.
KEEPS WELL.

title: red lobster garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese.
Stir for about 30 seconds until you have a soft dough.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix melted butter or margarine and garlic powder.
Brush this mixture on top of biscuits while they are still warm.
This will make 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: easiest-ever candy
directions: Place all ingredients in microwavable bowl.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Stir.
Spread in buttered dish.
Cool. Cut in squares.

title: diet coke chicken
directions: Spray Pam in frying pan on medium heat.
Brown chicken on both sides, remove chicken from pan.
Stir diet Coke and ketchup in pan until boiling.
Place chicken in mixture and cook for 30 minutes on medium to low heat.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel and cut eggs in halves.
Mash yolks with fork.
Mix yolks, onions, mustard, pickles and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk for 30 minutes.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sugar and mix.
Add cooled shortening.
Add flour sifted with baking powder, salt and soda.
Fill greased muffin pans two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix first two ingredients together by spoon and then add the Cool Whip and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: In a large pan saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add basil, oregano and tomato sauce.
Add water to fill pot 3/4 full. Let it cook several hours; add water if it cooks too thick.
Add sugar to taste; add salt and pepper to taste.
Lastly, add meat and let it cook until sauce is somewhat thick (not too thick). The longer it cooks the better it tastes.
If adding ground meat, cook separate to get rid of grease, then add to sauce.
Sausage may be added with tomato sauce right away.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs 1/2 hour.
Pour off water and cover with cold water. Let stand for 15 or 20 minutes.
Peel, cut lengthwise, remove yolks, mash and mix with mayo, sugar, lemon juice, relish and mustard.
Stuff whites of eggs; place slice of olive in center of each half egg.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: "dirt" dessert
directions: Blend the cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
In another bowl, mix the pudding and milk together.
Combine both bowls together. Add the Cool Whip.
Process the cookies in a food processor until the white center isn't visible.
Layer filling and cookie mixture; end up with the Oreo dirt on top in a foil lined clay flowerpot. Place an artificial flower in the center and serve.

title: garlic rice
directions: Soak the rice in water (which has had 2 teaspoons salt added) for at least 4 hours.
Strain and wash rice.
Drain.
Melt Crisco in pan.
Thinly slice garlic.
Add garlic, drained rice and 2 teaspoons salt to melted Crisco.
When rice starts to stick to pan, add water.
Cover when comes to a boil, turn down and simmer until water is absorbed, approximately 40 minutes.

title: kiwi and prosciutto
directions: Wrap kiwi quarters with slices of Prosciutto.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: christmas chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour and salt.
Melt butter in skillet.
Place chicken in skillet; turn once.
Separately, combine all other ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Pour mixture over chicken in skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 35 to 40 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Serves 4 nicely.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Cook apricots in boiling water to cover just until tender (about 35 minutes).
Drain and dice.
Mix apricots, cheese and extract together. Mix in 1/2 cup coconut.
Shape into small balls and roll in remaining crust.
Chill. Makes 24 balls.

title: blackberry cake(west virginia favorite)
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs (one at a time) and berries (juice and all).
Sift together flour, soda and a little cinnamon.
Mix and bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried vidalia onions
directions: Cut onions into rings and dip into batter; fry until light brown.
Add salt to suit your taste.

title: cabbage noodle salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add dressing before serving.
Will keep well overnight, but noodles will be softer.

title: milk chocolate icing
directions: Bring cocoa and butter to boil over low heat.
Boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add confectioners sugar and milk.
Mix to spreading consistency.

title: summer fruit bowl
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook water, sugar and lime juice 15 minutes or until mixture becomes a light syrup. Stir in mint leaves; cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and food coloring, if desired; mix well.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package.
Using large mixing bowl, add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the pudding mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spoon into pie shell. Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: quick blueberry muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, mix ice cream and flour.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into 6 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins test done.
While hot, brush muffin tops with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm. Yield:
6 muffins.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine ham, pineapple, celery and raisins in bowl.
Add mayonnaise and dry mustard; mix well.
Chill until serving time. Yields 4 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, pecans, salt, vanilla, sugar, syrup and butter together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place in oven preheated to 350°.
Lower heat to 325° and cook 50 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: easy sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: gorgeous fries
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into 1/2 inch wide sticks.
Put in ice water for 1/2 hour.
Drain and dry.
Arrange on cookie sheet. Slice butter and scatter over potatoes.
Sprinkle onion salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, tossing with spatula every 10 to 15 minutes.
Five minutes before removing, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Preparation:
30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Serve with sweet and sour dressing.

title: wild west beans
directions: Cook combined ingredients in heavy saucepan, first bringing to a boil, then turning heat down to medium-low.
Cook about two hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
May be cooked in baking dish in oven at 300°, uncovered, for about two hours.

title: ma's bean dish
directions: Brown hamburger and mix onions, cheese and barbecue sauce with pork and beans in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Place cheese slices on top about 5 minutes before you remove from oven.
Cut biscuits in half and place around edges and bake until brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet covered with wax paper.

title: pineapple pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in uncooked crusts at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer bean dip in bowl. Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning. Layer on bean dip. Mix avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Layer in bowl. Mix green onions, tomatoes and olives. Spread in bowl. Top with Cheddar cheese. Use with tortilla chips.

title: mashed potatoes ol
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees. Make potatoes according to directions on package for 2 pouches. Stir in 3/4 cup of the onions. Spread with salsa and top with olives, cheese and remaining onions. Bake 3-5 minutes or until golden. Serve with sour cream and chopped fresh cilantro, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet grilled zucchini(low calorie)
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise about 1/3-inch thick, creating zucchini steaks.
Rub in Gordon's Grub Rub on both sides.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Grill on both sides over hot flame until light brown.
Serve as main dish or as a side vegetable dish.

title: maple bars
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and milk. Stir until shortening melts.
When mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add eggs.
Stir in 2 cups of flour.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups to 2 cups more flour, more if needed.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 2 hours.
Press down and roll out on slightly floured board 1/2-inch thick in a rectangle shape. Cut with a sharp knife.
Let rise uncovered to form a crust and double in bulk.
Fry a few at a time in deep fat, 365°, for about 3 minutes.
When it rises to the surface and turns brown, turn it over and brown.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
When warm, spread with icing.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix at medium speed for at least 15 minutes, sugar, eggs and margarine.
Spread over cracker crumbs. Top with sliced bananas and drained pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chopped cherries and nuts.

title: red chili enchilada sauce
directions: Saute garlic in hot bacon drippings in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in seasonings.
Gradually add tomato sauce and water; simmer about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix, and let set at least 2 hours.
Lasts a long time.

title: chicken salad mold
directions: Combine plain gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water and set aside for 5 minutes.
Then in double boiler combine gelatin, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Heat until smooth.
Add bacon.
Mix chicken mixture, mayonnaise mix and bacon bits, plus 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
Blend well and add salt.
Mix well and let stand in refrigerator 7 to 8 hours.
Can be made the day before.

title: tortillas(makes 12 shells)
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Work in shortening with a fork and stir in water until dough forms a ball.
Knead 2 minutes. Divide into 12 equal parts and cover balls with a moist cloth.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Roll out each ball about 7 inches.
Heat both sides on lightly greased skillet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese, peanut butter and sugar in a bowl.
Slowly add milk and blend well.
Add whipped topping.
Pour into crust. If desired, top with chopped peanuts or grated chocolate.
Freeze until firm.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to a boil and add bouillon cubes, garlic powder and pepper.
Add onions, celery, carrots and cabbage.
Boil gently and add potatoes.
Continue to boil until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes.
Cook gently just until heated through.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend all ingredients, except eggs. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured for 1 hour. Glaze while hot.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes, peel side down, in 2 shallow baking pans. Mix remaining ingredients and brush potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush occasionally with mixture.

title: pineapple chicken bake
directions: Brush chicken with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: trifle (scottish version)(serves 20 to 25)
directions: Line the bottom of a glass bowl with ladyfingers, then pour sherry over them.
Drain fruit and place on top of ladyfingers. Make red Jell-O and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate until set.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Cook the rutabaga until soft (about 20 minutes) in salted water to cover; drain and mash.
Soak the bread crumbs in the cream and stir in the nutmeg, salt and beaten eggs; combine with the rutabaga.
Turn into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole, dot with butter and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups of grated Cheddar cheese. Bake 22 minutes at 400° in casserole.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir hamburger in skillet over medium heat until light brown; drain grease.
Stir in onion, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cover; set aside.
Heat remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.

title: mock chicken loaf
directions: Saute Soyameat, potatoes, celery, onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and turn into a well-greased casserole or loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: grandma bradburn's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and beat.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately and beat.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix topping ingredients with a fork and sprinkle on top of batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli terrific
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2-quart casserole.

title: easy chicken
directions: Use boneless and skinless chicken breasts.
Cut in small pieces, if desired, or leave whole.
Place in a baking dish.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Dissolve 2 squares of unsweetened chocolate in 1 cup of boiling water. Cool.

title: easy bean soup
directions: Place beans in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Cover with 6 to 8 cups water.
Heat to boiling; simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cover; let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham hocks, onion, garlic, parsley, salt, basil, pepper, nutmeg, oregano and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Add carrots, celery and potato flakes; mix well.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until carrots and celery are tender.
Remove ham; cut meat from bone.
Return meat to soup; heat and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Beat egg white until soft peaks form.
Continue beating and gradually add vanilla and brown sugar.
Fold in pecans.
Place pecan halves (well coated in sugar mixture) on lightly greased baking sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes. Turn off oven and leave in oven an additional 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: parmesan baked chicken
directions: Mix together corn flake crumbs, seasoned salt, dried parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in melted gutter, then in crumbs.
Place in a 350° oven for 1 hour; cover loosely with foil.

title: pearl's perfect potato salad (party size)
directions: Peel and chop potatoes; rinse.
In large pot, cover potatoes with water.
Add dash of salt.
Boil until tender.
Place eggs in pot.
Cover with water; add a dash of salt.
Boil until hard-boiled.
Drain potatoes and eggs when done; refrigerate to cool.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together. Drain raisins and dust with flour. Combine with fruit, carrots and nuts. Mix flour mixture with fruit/nut mixture. Mix eggs, oil and vanilla and add to mixture. Gently mix until all ingredients are moistened. Don't overmix! Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (depending on size) until done. Do not fill cups more than 2/3 full in muffin pan. Recipe should yield approximately 50+ muffins.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Soak tomatoes in boiling water 10 minutes; drain and add half in pie shell.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Layer on tomatoes.
Add more tomatoes and dry ingredients.
Add juice and peel of lemon and the butter.
Top with dough.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 35 minutes.
Put pan under pie, as it is very juicy.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Place
mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cook until
brown.
Let cool.
While crust is cooking, mix together Cool
Whip,
cream
cheese
and powdered sugar.
When crust is cool,
spread mixture over top, then add cherry pie filling on top.

title: janey's toffee bars
directions: Separate graham crackers and cover bottom of a large rectangular pan, which has been lined with waxed paper.
Bring the butter to a boil and then add brown sugar, constantly stirring. This should boil for about 2 minutes until the sugar has dissolved.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour mixture over crackers. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cut while warm.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press in pan.
Grease bottom and sides of pan.
Then mix the other ingredients and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans quesadillas
directions: Lay out 6 of the tortillas and sprinkle with cheese, onions, peppers and baked beans. Add another layer of cheese and top with remaining tortillas. Cook on warm grill for 3 minutes on each side or until warm throughout. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: pioneer cream pie(shallow, rich pie from frontier days)
directions: Combine sugars and flour, mixing well.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Pour into thoroughly chilled pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until silver knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack and refrigerate until serving time.

title: mom's throw it all together hamburger
directions: In separate skillet from meat, fry squash and potatoes until done. Mix in with hamburger meat. Serve. Great with fresh, sliced tomatoes.

title: potato-leek soup(low-fat)
directions: Cook veggies in enough water to prevent them from sticking, until they are tender.
Remove veggies from water and reserve it. Puree veggies in food processor or blender.
Return puree to pot and add chicken broth to reach desired consistency.
Some of reserved water may also be used, if needed to dilute puree.

title: salmon stuffed pepper
directions: Cut the tops off of the peppers and remove seeds.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 3-5 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Set aside.
Broil salmon 4-6 inches from heat for 4-5 minutes. Discard bones and skin.
Flake with fork on each side.
In large skillet, combine broth, leek, jalapenos, cilantro, worcestershire sauce and spices.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in rice, tartar sauce and sour cream.
Fold in salmon.
Spoon into peppers.
Place in an ungreased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until peppers are tender and filling is hot.
Yield 6 servings.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Blend cheese with enough mayonnaise to make a soft spread. Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on whole wheat bread.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill 1 hour.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Layer pineapple in bottom of baking dish. Cover with cheese, top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice. Pour over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown-cheese casserole
directions: In a large bowl, add hash browns, sour cream, onion, margarine, salt, pepper, soup and cheese; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together saving some crumbs and 1/4 cup of the butter for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine rolled oats, sugar, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add butter or margarine and blend well.
Arrange the apples in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread oatmeal mixture on the top of apples and press lightly.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender in a 350° oven (glass pan 325°).

title: cranberry-jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange together and mix in 3 to 4 packages of sweetener (optional).
Refrigerate for a few hours.

title: chicken coating(like the colonel's)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and coat chicken.
Dip in milk and re-coat.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes in 1/2 pound of butter.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls and cook in hot oil until brown.

title: arthur treacher's fish batter
directions: Soak fish in enough buttermilk to cover; place lemon slice on top and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Drain off milk and roll fish in dry pancake mix.
In another bowl, mix pancake mix and club soda until smooth like buttermilk.
Dip fish in batter and deep fry.

title: sea foam icing
directions: Beat all but vanilla in double boiler.
Beat until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Continue beating until stiff enough to spread.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients above, then add 1 can of shrimp. Chill.

title: chicken salad delight
directions: Stir together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry winks
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.
Shape level measuring tablespoon of dough into balls. Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Top each with cherry quarter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: grilled sweet potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, heat 1 1/2 cups water to boiling.
Add potato slices.
Cook until almost tender, 7 to 8 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt butter with oil.
Remove from heat.
In a cup, mix the rosemary, salt and pepper.
Arrange potato slices in a circle on pieces of foil, slightly overlapping the potatoes.
Drizzle each portion with some of the butter mixture and with the rosemary mixture.
Bring the sides of foil together to form a packet.
Arrange on grill on broiler and cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream softened margarine and sugar.
Add buttermilk and eggs. Mix, then add vanilla and coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Mix dressing at least 1 hour in advance.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli in least amount of water possible.
Salt to taste.
Place cooked broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with 1 can cream of celery soup.
Lay cheese slices over all. Prepare a large box of stuffing mix and spoon over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with salt in small amount of water until tender.
Add milk and cheese.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water until dissolved.
Add to potatoes.
Stir and cook slow until thickened.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients.
Spread on meat. Roll up and freeze.
Slice into thirds.
Thaw before serving.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a bowl and add crackers; toss well.
Drizzle oil over cracker mixture.
Stir well.
Place mixture in large paper bag; fold bag to close and let stand 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally.
Store in airtight container. (Put clothespin on bag to seal tight.)

title: sausage squares
directions: Grease oblong baking dish.
Cook sausage and onions until brown.
Drain excess grease.
Mix Bisquick, milk and 1 egg. Spread in dish.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Spread sausage mixture over dough.
Beat 1 egg with sour cream until well mixed. Spread over mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cookies cool, then cut into squares to serve.
Makes 16 to 24 squares.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper, onion and sugar together in large bowl. Bring the vinegar, salad oil, celery seed and salt to a boil. Pour over first ingredients and mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place chicken on top of mixture, skin side up (salt and peppered).
Sprinkle over chicken one envelope of dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and cook 3 hours at 325°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown pieces of chicken in electric skillet; add onion, carrots, water and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Cook about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from pan; add more water.
Bring to a boil.
Make dumplings according to directions on Bisquick box.
Remove dumplings and make sure there's at least 1 to 1 1/2 cups of liquid left.
You may need to add more water.
Add soup and bring to a boil.
Can be served with noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: baked venison steak
directions: Cut meat into 5-inch strips (1 inch thick).
Pour with tenderizing hammer.
Blend eggs and dip meat in egg.
Roll meat in cracker crumbs.
Cover bottom of frying pan with oil and preheat on medium setting.
Place meat in pan and brown both sides.
After browning, arrange strips in baking dish.
Add water until meat is almost covered.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Use the baking dish drippings to make gravy.

title: rice-chicken and cheese
directions: Chop onion; cook in oil until tender.
Add water or broth. Heat to boiling; add rice.
Lower heat; cover and cook slowly 20 minutes.
Add chicken, cheese, salt and pepper and cook over very low heat until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings, about 2/3 cup each.

title: fruit squares
directions: Combine together and add to dry ingredients and save a little milk and egg mixture to brush on top.
Divide dough into 2 parts; roll to fit cookie sheet (12 x 14-inch).
Spread with fruit and cover with other half of dough.
Brush top with milk and egg mixture.
If desired, you can sprinkle with coconut or finely chopped nuts or table sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bar cookies
directions: Mix and press into square baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender. Add to broccoli.
Mix in mushroom soup and the cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and well blended.
A squeeze of lemon juice helps to retain the nice green color.
Serve in chafing dish with tostados, Fritos or toast rounds.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat well together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: good cake
directions: Mix nuts, cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour evenly over the above.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool, then cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: jog in a jug
directions: Mix and drink 2 ounces per day.
Keep refrigerated.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground beef & onion. Add brown sugar & BBQ sauce. Press biscuit dough into ungreased muffin pans, making sure dough goes up sides. Spoon meat into cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes. Yield: 12 cups.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Mix all and form into a ball.

title: reese's cup dessert(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Dip in melted chocolate chips.
Refrigerate until hard.

title: chicken terrapin
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; thicken with the flour.
Boil good.
Add remaining ingredients; stir easily as eggs and peas will mash.
If peppers are used, cook and drain.
Serve over hot chow mein noodles.
This can be frozen and served later.

title: upside down german chocolate cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put coconut and nuts in bottom of pan. Mix cake as directed.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sassafras tea
directions: Dig sassafras roots.
Clean well and cut in small pieces. Better to let dry before using.
Boil roots in water until it reaches the strength you want.
Add sugar to taste.
Good for what ails you.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Place mixture in tube pan. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spray an 8 or 9-inch cake pan with Pam and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes approximately 24 appetizer servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water. Add fruits with juices and pecans. Chill until set.

Bake in a warm oven.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual.
Saute onion and celery.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refreshing iced tea
directions: Add ice to glass.
Pour in iced tea.
Add a slice of lemon for a bitter sweet experience.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Yields - 2 cups of Icing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into pie shell and cook until done.

title: helen's french drop doughnuts
directions: Place water, sugar, rind and butter in a heavy saucepan and bring to the boiling point.
Add flour and salt all at once; cook for a minute or two, stirring constantly, until mixture leaves the side of the pan.
Turn into a bowl and let cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with a rotary or electric mixer, until mixture is smooth.
Drop from a teaspoon into 365° hot oil, frying 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Cool slightly before rolling in sugar.
These are "melt in your mouth delicious".

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Stir in Cool Whip. Use graham cracker pie crust.
Chill until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O, gelatin and sugar together and add to boiling water, stirring until dissolved. Then add the cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and orange juice. Pour into bowl and chill in refrigerator until firm. Will keep for several days.

title: kirk's queso dip
directions: Put cheese in crock-pot to melt.
Add can of tomatoes and chilies.
Mix together.
Serve with nacho chips.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: ham and cheddar skillet pie
directions: Mix together Bisquick, milk, salt, pepper and eggs.
It will be a little lumpy.
Stir in ham, onion and green pepper.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box.
Add bananas and walnut pieces to batter.
Cake will be moist.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits and set aside.
In large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Add orange juice and sour cream; mix well.
Add canned fruit and cherries; stir gently.
Add apples and bananas last.

title: baked brisket
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer. Sprinkle liberally with other salts. Mix liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce; pour over meat. Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Turn after 12 hours. Bake, covered, at 225° for 6 to 8 hours. Drain before serving. Do not serve juice. Slice thin.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine egg and water. By hand, stir in brownie mix. Mix well. Fill paper lined or greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until soft touch.
Cool completely.
Frost as desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding, fold in cool whip and eagle brand milk.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas alternately.
Cover the top with cool whip.

title: hawaiian coconut pineapple bread
directions: Put all ingredients into your bread maker pan in the order listed or according to the manufacturer's instructions. Select "white bread" and push start.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and set overnight.
Use round loaf of bread.
Hollow out center and fill with dip.
Use center of bread or crackers to serve dip.
We use tortilla chips.

title: cherry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch dish with Pam. Pour cherry pie filling into oblong dish.
Pour crushed pineapple on top of cherry pie filling.
Spread yellow cake mix evenly for third layer.
Top with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
